%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meet%20Justin%20Breen%2C%20a%20top%20lawyer%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20the%20private-credit%20boom%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Justin%20Breen%20on%20a%20dark%20blue%20background%20with%20lines%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65773f6c7a3c8094d5dba676%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJustin%20Breen%2C%20partner%20at%20the%20law%20firm%20Proskauer.%3Cp%3EProskauer%3B%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJustin%20Breen%2C%20an%20attorney%20at%20the%20law%20firm%20Proskauer%2C%20is%20a%20go-to%20private-credit%20lawyer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFirst%20focusing%20on%20banks%2C%20now%20asset%20managers%2C%20his%20career%20has%20traced%20the%20market's%20growth.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20now%20advises%20large%20private-credit%20firms%2C%20including%20Ares%20Capital%20and%20Bain%20Capital.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJustin%20Breen's%20legal%20career%20has%20traced%20the%20arc%20of%20the%20rapidly%20expanding%20private-credit%20market.%20When%20he%20started%20out%20some%2020%20years%20ago%2C%20he%20worked%20primarily%20with%20banks%20that%20were%20underwriting%20company%20loans.%20Now%2C%20he%20focuses%20almost%20exclusively%20on%20private%20credit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20counsels%20the%20biggest%20names%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-credit-toast-of-the-town-greenwich-economic-forum-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprivate%20credit%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Ares%20Capital%2C%20Golub%20Capital%2C%20Bain%20Capital%2C%20and%20Churchill%20Asset%20Management.%20He's%20closed%20finance%20deals%20worth%20some%20%24100%20billion%20and%20coordinated%20debt%20for%20European%20football%20clubs%20including%20Atl%C3%A9tico%20Madrid%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20carmaker%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ff1-drivers-weight-limit-fitness-training-diet-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFormula%201%20competitor%3C%2Fa%3E%20McLaren.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20lending%20to%20the%20thousands%20of%20businesses%20in%20the%20so-called%20middle%20market%20(filled%20with%20companies%20that%20aren't%20tiny%20startups%2C%20but%20aren't%20large%20public%20corporations%2C%20either)%20has%20shifted%20outside%20the%20traditional%20banking%20system%2C%20private-equity%20firms'%20private-credit%20arms%20have%20sought%20out%20bigger%20teams%20of%20experts%20and%20lawyers%20to%20help%20them%20get%20deals%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBreen%20is%20a%20partner%20at%20the%20law%20firm%20Proskauer%2C%20where%20he%20leads%20the%20firm's%20global%20finance%20practice%20as%20a%20go-to%20lawyer%20advising%20influential%20money%20managers%20in%20a%20space%20that%20analysts%20expect%20to%20grow%20by%20multiples.%20Investment%20firms%20have%20eaten%20into%20banks'%20share%20of%20the%20loan%20market%2C%20extending%20credit%20to%20companies%20that%20are%20considered%20too%20risky%20for%20banks%20to%20lend%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBreen%20describes%20himself%20as%20a%20collaborative%20dealmaker.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20an%20industry%20that%20doesn't%20lack%20for%20egos%2C%20but%20it's%20really%20not%20about%20us.%20We%20are%20there%20to%20help%20facilitate%20resolutions%2C%20come%20to%20a%20good%20deal%2C%20help%20our%20clients%20put%20money%20to%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recently%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'd%20love%20to%20say%20that%20I%20was%20prescient%20and%20knew%20exactly%20what%20the%20market%20was%20going%20to%20turn%20into.%20I'm%20not%20sure%20anybody%20fully%20appreciated%20it%20would%20turn%20into%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20interview%20has%20been%20lightly%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou've%20been%20at%20Proskauer%20for%20about%2013%20years%2C%20and%20during%20that%20time%20you've%20seen%20tremendous%20growth%20in%20the%20private-credit%20market.%20What%20has%20your%20path%20been%20like%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202002%2C%20I%20started%20my%20career%20at%20Cahill%20Gordon%2C%20a%20market%20leader%20in%20the%20syndicated%20bank%20bond%20space.%20When%20I%20was%20there%2C%20I%20would%20say%20that%20about%20two-thirds%20of%20my%20practice%20was%20really%20representing%20investment%20banks%20in%20the%20syndicated%20bank%20bond%20world%3A%20sponsors%20buying%20a%20company%2C%20needing%20committed%20financing%2C%20and%20using%20a%20bank%20bridge%20that%20hopefully%20turns%20into%20a%20successful%20bond%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20smaller%20checks%20than%20you%20see%20now%2C%20but%20I'd%20like%20to%20think%20I%20saw%20enough%20of%20the%20deal%20flow%20where%20the%20check%20sizes%20were%20getting%20bigger%20and%20bigger.%20You%20had%20to%20take%20notice%20of%20how%20prominent%20it%20was%20becoming%2C%20and%20the%20players%20involved%20kept%20increasing.%20In%202010%2C%20I%20was%20approached%20by%20Proskauer%20to%20come%20here%2C%20and%20it%20was%20a%20really%20good%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20love%20to%20say%20that%20I%20was%20prescient%20and%20knew%20exactly%20what%20the%20market%20was%20going%20to%20turn%20into.%20I'm%20not%20sure%20anybody%20fully%20appreciated%20it%20would%20turn%20into%20this.%20There%20was%20certainly%20a%20lot%20of%20right%20place%2C%20right%20time%2C%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20luck%20involved%2C%20but%20right%20when%20I%20came%20here%20in%202010%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20the%20faucet%20really%20turned%20on.%20I%20started%20off%20working%20somewhat%20with%20banks%2C%20and%20a%20portion%20of%20my%20practice%20was%20still%20with%20banks%2C%20and%20back%20then%2C%20maybe%2050%25%20was%20with%20asset%20managers.%20Over%20time%2C%20the%20market%20has%20matured%20to%20where%20almost%20everything%20I%20do%20now%20is%20with%20asset%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20mentioned%20that%20it's%20a%20really%20competitive%20market%20right%20now%2C%20and%20even%20that%20feels%20like%20an%20understatement.%20How%20has%20the%20private-credit%20market%20changed%20over%20your%20career%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20market%20has%20changed%20drastically.%20I%20think%20the%20easy%20answer%20is%20there's%20just%20a%20lot%20more%20money.%20So%20there%20are%20more%20investors%20investing%20in%20these%20asset%20managers%2C%20which%20allows%20the%20asset%20managers%20to%20then%20put%20more%20money%20out.%20The%20deals%20sort%20of%20keep%20getting%20bigger%20and%20bigger%3A%20%242%20billion%2C%20%243%20billion%2C%20%244%20billion%2C%20%245%20billion%20deals%20competing%20with%20that%20syndicated%20bank%20bond%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20the%20interesting%20thing%20about%20the%20competitive%20dynamic%20is%20that%20the%20level%20has%20just%20dramatically%20increased.%20Twenty%20years%20ago%2C%20private-equity%20sponsors%20rarely%20had%20people%20who%20were%20dedicated%20to%20doing%20these%20transactions.%20They%20relied%20entirely%20on%20their%20lawyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20every%20major%20private-equity%20firm%20has%20not%20only%20one%20or%20two%20but%20sometimes%20complete%20teams%20of%20debt%20capital%20markets%20experts.%20Their%20sole%20roles%20are%20facilitating%20a%20competitive%20process%20on%20these%20financings%2C%20to%20push%20the%20terms%20in%20a%20way%20that%20makes%20sense%20for%20them%20to%20create%20a%20really%20competitive%20market%20dynamic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20a%20deal%2C%20or%20a%20type%20of%20deal%2C%20that%20was%20particularly%20rewarding%20for%20you%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20we%20had%20a%20client%20come%20to%20us%20and%20they%20were%20interested%20in%20potentially%20looking%20at%20making%20investments%20in%20the%20sports%2C%20media%2C%20and%20entertainment%20space%2C%20which%20for%20us%20couldn't%20have%20fit%20better%20into%20our%20firm%20and%20what%20we%20do.%20So%20we%20started%20having%20conversations%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFast-forward%20three%20years%20later%2C%20we've%20helped%20them%20form%20the%20fund.%20We've%20done%20a%20bunch%20of%20investments.%20As%20an%20avid%20sports%20fan%2C%20it's%20personally%20a%20lot%20of%20fun.%20It's%20something%20kind%20of%20new.%20But%20again%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20one%20of%20those%20things%20that%20just%20kind%20of%20highlights%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20private-credit%20product%20because%20it%20allows%20the%20flexibility%20to%20invest%20in%20US%20sports%20teams%20and%20European%20sports%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20sport%20has%20its%20own%20unique%20sort%20of%20rules%20and%20regulations.%20Threading%20the%20needle%20and%20finding%20a%20way%20to%20help%20our%20clients%20make%20those%20investments%20that%20fit%20within%20that%20rubric%2C%20while%20also%20sticking%20to%20their%20investment%20guidelines%2C%20has%20been%20a%20lot%20of%20fun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20would%20you%20say%20are%20the%20biggest%20risks%20that%20your%20private-credit%20clients%20face%20today%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20almost%20flip%20the%20question%20because%20I%20think%20the%20reality%20is%20the%20resilience%20of%20this%20product%20has%20shown%20despite%20all%20of%20the%20risks.%20So%20we%20lived%20through%20COVID%2C%20we%20lived%20through%20a%20bunch%20of%20different%20things%20that%20have%20come%20up%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20including%20what%20happened%20with%20Silicon%20Valley%20Bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20living%20in%20a%20rising%20rate%20environment%2C%20and%20I%20think%20people%20keep%20looking%20for%20reasons%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20the%20private-credit%20market%2C%20here%20it%20is%20%E2%80%94%20with%20rising%20rates%2C%20this%20is%20going%20to%20hurt.%26quot%3B%20And%20it%20really%20hasn't%20happened.%20The%20product%20has%20been%20really%20resilient.%20Loss%20ratios%20are%20super%20low%2C%20default%20rates%20are%20really%20low.%20I%20think%20because%20of%20the%20relationship%20aspect%20with%20some%20of%20this%20stuff%2C%20when%20you%20do%20have%20companies%20that%20aren't%20in%20great%20shape%2C%20it's%20not%20always%20a%20race%20to%20the%20bottom.%20There's%20a%20real%20discussion%20between%20sophisticated%20institutions%20as%20to%20what%20they're%20going%20to%20do%20to%20fix%20that%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20it's%20not%20fixable%2C%20and%20our%20clients%20need%20to%20take%20it%20over.%20Every%20once%20in%20a%20great%20while%2C%20a%20company%20goes%20through%20a%20bankruptcy.%20But%20by%20and%20large%2C%20in%20this%20industry%2C%20almost%20everything%20is%20an%20out-of-court%20workout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20mean%20that%20if%20there's%20trouble%20at%20a%20company%2C%20it's%20more%20likely%20that%20the%20sponsor%20can%20work%20out%20something%20like%20a%20repayment%20plan%20behind%20closed%20doors%20rather%20than%20going%20through%20a%20bankruptcy%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExactly.%20Sometimes%2C%20a%20lender%20might%20make%20concessions%20and%20defer%20some%20of%20the%20cash%20interest%20for%20a%20period%20of%20time%2C%20or%20change%20some%20of%20the%20covenant%20restrictions%20for%20a%20certain%20period%20of%20time%20in%20exchange%20for%20some%20additional%20economics%2C%20some%20other%20rights.%20Sometimes%20the%20sponsor%20might%20put%20in%20some%20of%20their%20own%20money%20to%20help%20see%20a%20company%20through%20a%20rough%20patch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20the%20lenders%20do%20it.%20There's%20usually%20a%20conversation%20about%20all%20this%20stuff%20that%20I%20think%20really%20facilitates%20a%20better%20result.%20I%20think%20that's%20proven%20true.%20The%20default%20rates%20are%2C%20notwithstanding%20the%20current%20environment%2C%20still%20historically%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThey%20are%2C%20and%20they%20are%20expected%20to%20rise.%20Your%20firm's%20index%20that%20tracks%20private-credit%20defaults%20showed%20that%20while%20the%20overall%20default%20rate%20fell%20to%201.4%25%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20defaults%20rose%20for%20some%20subsets%20of%20borrowers.%20With%20more%20companies%20facing%20more%20expensive%20debt%20loads%2C%20can%20you%20walk%20through%20what%20happens%20between%20a%20private%20lender%20and%20a%20company%20in%20trouble%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20short%20answer%20is%20that%20every%20situation%20is%20different%2C%20but%20one%20of%20the%20interesting%20things%20about%20the%20private-credit%20market%20is%20that%2C%20unlike%20the%20syndicated%20market%2C%20there%20is%20still%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20the%20market%20where%20there%20is%20a%20financial%20maintenance%20covenant%20tested%20quarterly.%20The%20borrower%20will%20send%20in%20a%20compliance%20certificate%20showing%20the%20EBITDA%2C%20the%20debt%2C%20the%20leverage%20ratios%2C%20and%20things%20like%20that.%20And%20because%20of%20that%2C%20lenders%20usually%20have%20a%20clearer%20picture%20of%20what%20the%20company's%20performance%20is%20looking%20like%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'll%20admit%2C%20it's%20a%20clich%C3%A9%20to%20end%20an%20interview%20by%20asking%20where%20you%20think%20the%20market%20is%20going%2C%20but%20I%20think%20with%20the%20aggressive%20expansion%20of%20private%20credit%2C%20it's%20a%20question%20worth%20asking.%20What%20will%20fund%20managers%20come%20up%20with%20next%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20see%20any%20signs%20that%20the%20market%20is%20slowing%20down%20%E2%80%94%20just%20the%20opposite.%20I%20think%20expansion%20isn't%20only%20in%20the%20different%20products%20they're%20offering%2C%20which%20isn't%20necessarily%20front-page%20news%20like%20a%20sponsor%20buying%20a%20company%2C%20but%20we're%20doing%20private-credit%20financings%20for%20clients%20in%20different%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20we%20have%20clients%20who%20have%20dedicated%20healthcare%20funds%2C%20dedicated%20sports%20funds%2C%20you%20name%20it.%20We're%20also%20seeing%20different%20types%20of%20products.%20There's%20a%20real%20flight%20to%20financing%20real%20assets.%20There's%20a%20real%20interest%20in%20infrastructure%20debt%2C%20real-estate%20financings%2C%20alternative%20credits%2C%20NAV%20loans%2C%20you%20name%20it.%20Asset%20managers%20and%20our%20clients%20are%20really%20focused%20on%20expanding%20that%20offering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-justin-breen-proskauer-lawyer-private-credit-boom-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702477306000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65773f6c7a3c8094d5dba676%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-justin-breen-proskauer-lawyer-private-credit-boom-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Justin%20Breen's%20legal%20career%20has%20traced%20the%20shift%20from%20banks%20being%20the%20go-to%20lenders%20for%20corporate%20America%20to%20private%20equity%20players.%20He%20spoke%20to%20Business%20Insider%20about%20his%20path%20and%20predictions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22rungarino%40businessinsider.com%20(Rebecca%20Ungarino)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-justin-breen-proskauer-lawyer-private-credit-boom-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Microsoft%2C%20OpenAI's%20biggest%20stan%2C%20shows%20off%20its%20own%20smaller%20AI%20models%20that%20could%20rival%20ChatGPT%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225751%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Microsoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655c2d0d4ca513d8242ca8f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223749%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMicrosoft%20CEO%2