3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20Telegraph%20reported%20Tuesday%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Steve%20New%2C%20who%20teaches%20a%20module%20on%20technology%20and%20operations%20management%2C%20told%20The%20Telegraph%20that%20undergraduates%20studying%20Economics%20and%20Management%20were%20made%20to%20undertake%20the%20task%20in%20his%20class%20and%20that%20it%20wouldn't%20be%20part%20of%20any%20formal%20assessment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20explained%20that%20when%20AI%20tools%20are%20used%20%26quot%3Bthoughtfully%20and%20critically%26quot%3B%20it%20%26quot%3Bshould%20help%20you%20produce%20a%20much%20better%20essay%20than%20you%20would%20produce%20unaided.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20note%20on%20the%20course%20said%20that%20the%20assignment%20has%20been%20adapted%20to%20the%20current%20academic%20year%20because%20of%20how%20generative%20AI%20systems%20like%20ChatGPT%2C%20Bard%2C%20and%20Claude%20have%20%26quot%3Bchanged%20the%20environment%20in%20which%20we%20work.%26quot%3B%20It%20said%20that%20AI%20tools%20%26quot%3Bcan%20greatly%20enhance%20your%20ability%20to%20generate%20essays%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20OpenAI%20released%20ChatGPT%20to%20the%20public%20in%20November%202022%2C%20college%20professors%20saw%20a%20sharp%20rise%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-essays-college-cheating-professors-caught-students-ai-plagiarism-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estudents%20using%20the%20chatbot%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20write%20assignments.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20two%20philosophy%20professors%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20assignments%20written%20by%20ChatGPT%20raised%20red%20flags%20because%20they're%20really%20%26quot%3Bwell-written%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20surface%20but%20upon%20closer%20examination%2C%20they%20made%20no%20sense%20or%20lacked%20context%20and%20depth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-chatgpt-colleges-students-professors-education-cheat-exams-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ERussell%20Group%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20group%20of%2024%20leading%20colleges%20in%20the%20UK%20including%20Oxford%20and%20Cambridge%2C%20agreed%20to%20a%20set%20of%20principles%20that%20would%20allow%20students%20and%20teachers%20to%20become%20%26quot%3BAI-literate%26quot%3B%20and%20use%20the%20technology%20ethically.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20New's%20class%2C%20the%20students%20were%20told%20to%20write%20out%20an%20answer%20to%20an%20essay%20question%20using%20an%20AI%20tool%20of%20their%20choice%2C%20and%20then%20pass%20it%20on%20to%20their%20course%20mates%20for%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20course%20mates%20would%20fact-check%20their%20essays%20because%20AI%20tools%20have%20frequently%20made%20up%20facts%20and%20even%20used%20fake%20citations.%20The%20students%20were%20still%20subject%20to%20standard%20rules%20on%20referencing%20and%20plagiarism%20when%20writing%20the%20essay.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20told%20students%20that%20AI%20should%20%26quot%3Bincrease%20your%20ability%20to%20think%20hard%20about%20the%20subjects%20you%20discuss%2C%20and%20make%20you%20more%20confident%20in%20framing%20a%20clear%20and%20persuasive%20argument%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20document%20that%20emerges%20should%20be%20yours.%20You%20need%20to%20write%20stuff%20you%20will%20stand%20by.%20The%20AI%20can%20produce%20humdrum%20'some%20say%20this%2C%20some%20say%20that%E2%80%A6meh'%20essays%20in%20a%20fraction%20of%20a%20second%3B%20you%20should%20be%20producing%20compelling%2C%20tightly-argued%2C%20evidence-based%20prose%20that%20you%20believe%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20New%20said%20that%20AI%20tools%20can%20%26quot%3B%3Cspan%3Ehelp%20students%20think%20more%20deeply%20and%20more%20broadly%20about%20the%20issues%20under%20consideration.%20Th