0href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraines-tanks-are-back-in-action-to-defend-avdiivka-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAvdiikva%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmid%20steep%20casualties%2C%20Russia%20has%20launched%20a%20recruitment%20drive%20to%20strengthen%20its%20military%2C%20changed%20military%20rules%20to%20allow%20service%20members%20to%20serve%20for%20longer%2C%20and%20recruited%20prisoners%20to%20battalions%20used%20in%20head-on%20assaults%20on%20Ukrainian%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20also%20mobilized%20around%20300%2C000%20civilians%20into%20the%20military%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-lost-87-ground-troops-had-before-war-ukraine-cnn-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702468931000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65798d4950edbc52a863a3bc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-lost-87-ground-troops-had-before-war-ukraine-cnn-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20US%20intelligence%20briefing%20to%20Congress%20obtained%20by%20CNN%20detailed%20Russia's%20staggering%20losses%20in%20Ukraine.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tporter%40businessinsider.com%20(Tom%20Porter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A164%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-lost-87-ground-troops-had-before-war-ukraine-cnn-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Texas%20found%20startling%20amounts%20of%20a%20cancer-causing%20chemical%20in%20the%20air%20outside%20Houston.%20Nobody%20told%20the%20residents.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20tanker%20truck%20waits%20to%20be%20loaded%20with%20chemicals%20at%20K-Solv%2C%20a%20chemical%20distribution%20company%20nestled%20in%20a%20residential%20area%20in%20Channelview%2C%20Texas.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657899730ec98e92f74e9333%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20tanker%20truck%20waits%20to%20be%20loaded%20with%20chemicals%20at%20K-Solv%2C%20a%20chemical%20distribution%20company%20nestled%20in%20a%20residential%20area%20in%20Channelview%2C%20Texas.%20The%20Texas%20Commission%20on%20Environmental%20Quality%20repeatedly%20documented%20high%20levels%20of%20cancer-causing%20benzene%20downwind%20of%20the%20facility%20but%20has%20allowed%20the%20company%20to%20expand.%20Today%20K-Solv%20can%20legally%20release%2020%20times%20more%20volatile%20organic%20compounds%20%E2%80%94%20a%20class%20of%20chemicals%20that%20includes%20benzene%20%E2%80%94%20into%20the%20air%20each%20year%20than%20it%20did%20in%202005.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20reported%20by%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublichealthwatch.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EPublic%20Health%20Watch%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20nonprofit%2C%20nonpartisan%20investigative%20news%20organization.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECHANNELVIEW%2C%20Texas%20%E2%80%94%20For%20nearly%2020%20years%2C%20Texas%20environmental%20regulators%20have%20kept%20a%20disturbing%20secret.%20People%20living%20in%20a%20small%2C%20unincorporated%20community%20east%20of%20Houston%20are%20routinely%20breathing%20dangerous%20levels%20of%20benzene%2C%20a%20chemical%20linked%20to%20leukemia%20and%20other%20blood%20cancers.%20Emerging%20research%20also%20connects%20it%20to%20diabetes%20and%20reproductive%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Texas%20Commission%20on%20Environmental%20Quality%2C%20or%20TCEQ%2C%20has%20not%20told%20residents%20about%20the%20health%20risks%20they%20face.%20And%20it%20has%20done%20little%20to%20rein%20in%20the%20facility%20that%20the%20agency%20knew%20was%20releasing%20large%20amounts%20of%20benzene.%20Instead%2C%20the%20TCEQ%20has%20allowed%20K-Solv%2C%20a%20chemical%20distribution%20company%20nestled%20in%20Channelview's%20Jacintoport%20neighborhood%2C%20to%20expand%20its%20operations%20four%20times%20since%20the%20problem%20was%20discovered%20in%202005.%20Today%20K-Solv%20is%20legally%20allowed%20to%20release%20almost%2020%20times%20more%20volatile%20organic%20compounds%20%E2%80%94%20a%20class%20of%20chemicals%20that%20includes%20benzene%20%E2%80%94%20into%20the%20air%20each%20year%20than%20it%20did%20back%20then.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETCEQ%20documents%20obtained%20by%20Public%20Health%20Watch%20show%20that%20some%20of%20those%20early%20readings%20were%20double%20the%20level%20Texas%20considered%20safe%20at%20the%20time.%20Public%20Health%20Watch%20also%20analyzed%20more%20recent%20TCEQ%20pollution%20data%20and%20found%20that%20Channelview's%20benzene%20problem%20has%20only%20worsened%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBenzene%20is%20a%20colorless%2C%20sweet-smelling%20chemical%20found%20in%20crude%20oil%20and%20products%20including%20gasoline%2C%20solvents%2C%20plastics%2C%20paints%2C%20adhesives%2C%20and%20detergents.%20Although%20it%20has%20been%20linked%20to%20leukemia%20since%20the%20late%201920s%2C%20it%20is%20unevenly%20regulated%20because%20of%20relentless%20opposition%20from%20industry%20groups.%20When%20the%20federal%20government%20tried%20in%201978%20to%20enhance%20safeguards%20for%20workers%20exposed%20to%20benzene%2C%20the%20American%20Petroleum%20Institute%20fought%20the%20effort%20all%20the%20way%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20delaying%20new%20regulations%20for%20almost%2010%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221004%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Google%20Earth%20image%20of%20K-Solv's%20chemical%20distribution%20facility%20in%20Channelview's%20Jacintoport%20neighborhood.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578e25350edbc52a8638ff5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22661%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Google%20Earth%20image%20of%20K-Solv's%20chemical%20distribution%20facility%20in%20Channelview's%20Jacintoport%20neighborhood.%20Barges%20loaded%20with%20petrochemicals%20line%20the%20shores%20of%20the%20San%20Jacinto%20River.%3Cp%3EGoogle%20Earth%3B%20Landsat%2FCopernicus%3B%20Data%20SIO%3B%20National%20Oceanic%20and%20Atmospheric%20Administration%3B%20U.S.%20Navy%3B%20Geospatial-Intelligence%20Agency%3B%20General%20Bathymetric%20Chart%20of%20the%20Oceans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20benzene%20standard%20for%20workers%20today%20is%20the%20same%20as%20it%20was%20in%201987%2C%20although%20a%20growing%20body%20of%20evidence%20shows%20it%20doesn't%20give%20them%20nearly%20enough%20protection%20against%20cancer.%20And%20there%20are%20still%20no%20federal%20standards%20for%20ambient%20benzene%20exposure%20%E2%80%94%20the%20amount%20that%20people%20who%20live%20near%20industrial%20facilities%20can%20safely%20breathe%20as%20they%20go%20about%20their%20daily%20lives.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20eight%20states%2C%20including%20Texas%20and%20California%2C%20have%20tried%20to%20fill%20that%20gap%20by%20creating%20their%20own%20regulations%20to%20limit%20ambient%20benzene%20emissions.%20But%20while%20California%20has%20strengthened%20its%20rules%20over%20the%20years%2C%20Texas%20has%20gone%20in%20the%20opposite%20direction.%20Its%20guidelines%20are%20far%20weaker%20than%20those%20in%20any%20of%20the%20other%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20TCEQ%20says%20the%20public%20is%20protected%20if%20the%20air%20outside%20industrial%20facilities%20contains%20an%20average%20of%20no%20more%20than%20180%20parts%20of%20benzene%20per%20billion%20parts%20of%20air%20(180%20ppb)%20over%20a%20one-hour%20period.%20That's%20seven%20times%20higher%20than%20Texas%20said%20was%20safe%20back%20in%202005%2C%20when%20Channelview's%20benzene%20problem%20was%20discovered.%20It's%2022%20times%20higher%20than%20the%208%20ppb%20guideline%20California%20uses%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%20also%20has%20weakened%20its%20long-term%20guideline%20for%20benzene%20%E2%80%94%20a%20number%20meant%20to%20protect%20residents%20from%20the%20risk%20of%20developing%20cancer.%20In%202007%2C%20the%20TCEQ%20raised%20its%20annual%20guideline%20from%20an%20average%20of%201%20ppb%20to%201.4%20ppb%2C%20a%2040%25%20increase.%20That's%2014%20times%20more%20than%20what%20California%20says%20is%20safe%20and%20at%20least%203.5%20times%20higher%20than%20any%20other%20state%20allows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20TCEQ%20loosened%20its%20guidelines%20and%20more%20industries%20moved%20into%20Channelview's%20Jacintoport%20neighborhood%2C%20the%20community's%20benzene%20problem%20intensified.%20A%20Public%20Health%20Watch%20analysis%20of%20TCEQ%20pollution%20data%20shows%20that%20between%202019%20and%202021%2C%20annual%20readings%20soared%20as%20high%20as%202.1%20ppb%2C%20exceeding%20even%20today's%20weakened%20TCEQ%20guidelines%20by%2050%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20independent%20scientists%20who%20reviewed%20the%20Public%20Health%20Watch%20findings%20say%20those%20annual%20readings%20are%20especially%20troubling.%20While%20short-term%20emissions%20can%20cause%20immediate%20health%20problems%20like%20vomiting%20and%20drowsiness%2C%20high%20long-term%20emissions%20indicate%20consistent%2C%20daily%20exposures%20that%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cancer.org%2Fcancer%2Fcancer-causes%2Fbenzene.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elead%20to%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20life-threatening%20conditions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20chart%20of%20benzene%20levels%20in%20Channelview%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65789b9c7a3c8094d5dc1b9a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221184%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%20Community%20Health%20News%3B%20Texas%20Commission%20on%20Environmental%20Quality%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20exposure%20to%20a%20carcinogen%20increases%20your%20risk%20of%20developing%20cancer.%20We%20have%20to%20limit%20that%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20know%20why%20you%20wouldn't%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Loren%20Hopkins%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Rice%20University%20and%20a%20nationally%20recognized%20expert%20in%20environmental%20science.%20%26quot%3BWe%20already%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20carcinogens%20in%20our%20air.%20It%20doesn't%20make%20sense%20to%20me%20to%20increase%20the%20threshold%20for%20benzene.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20U.S.%20Environmental%20Protection%20Agency%20has%20created%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2FAirToxScreen%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etool%20that%20measures%20a%20community's%20increased%20cancer%20risk%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20toxic%20chemicals%20in%20the%20air.%20It%20shows%20that%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Texas%20the%20lifetime%20total%20cancer%20risk%20from%20exposure%20to%20chemicals%2C%20including%20benzene%2C%20is%2030%20cases%20in%201%20million%20people.%20In%20Channelview's%20Jacintoport%20neighborhood%2C%20where%20K-Solv%20and%20many%20other%20industries%20pollute%20the%20air%2C%20the%20risk%20is%20double%20that%3A%2060%20in%20a%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20likely%20an%20undercount%2C%26quot%3B%20Hopkins%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20EPA's%20National%20Air%20Toxics%20Assessment%20tool%20is%20based%20on%20weaker%20monitoring%20data%20from%20a%20few%20years%20back.%20We're%20seeing%20much%20higher%20benzene%20numbers%20in%20Jacintoport%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20newer%20benzene%20numbers%20she%20has%20seen%2C%20Hopkins%20thinks%20a%20more%20accurate%20cancer-risk%20figure%20for%20Jacintoport%20could%20be%20as%20high%20as%2078%20in%20a%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Children%20return%20home%20from%20school%20in%20Channelview%2C%20Texas.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65789d1b50edbc52a86359c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChildren%20return%20home%20from%20school%20in%20Channelview%2C%20Texas.%20Over%20the%20last%20four%20decades%2C%20the%20once-rural%20area%20has%20become%20increasingly%20industrialized.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Public%20Health%20Watch%2C%20the%20TCEQ%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bbenzene%20concentrations%20measured%20in%20the%20Jacintoport%20area%20since%202005%20have%20triggered%20actions%20at%20TCEQ%20that%20include%20placement%20of%20stationary%20air%20monitors%2C%20evaluation%20of%20air%20monitoring%20data%2C%20and%20follow-up%20investigations%20of%20potential%20pollutant%20sources.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJacintoport%20residents%20are%20well-protected%2C%20the%20statement%20said%2C%20because%20state%20guidelines%20are%20%26quot%3Bset%20at%20levels%20well%20below%20concentrations%20that%20would%20cause%20health%20effects.%26quot%3B%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tceq.texas.gov%2Fdownloads%2Ftoxicology%2Fdsd%2Ffinal%2Fbenzene.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20document%20on%20the%20TCEQ%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20guidelines%20are%20based%20on%20scientific%20studies%20from%20the%201980s%20and%20'90s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTCEQ%20continues%20to%20vigilantly%20evaluate%20benzene%20levels%20at%20%5Bthe%20Jacintoport%5D%20monitor%2C%20while%20encouraging%20efforts%20to%20reduce%20benzene%20in%20this%20area%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20agency%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJacintoport's%20plight%20shows%20what%20can%20happen%20when%20economic%20growth%20is%20prioritized%20over%20public%20health.%20TCEQ%20scientists%20documented%20harmful%20levels%20of%20air%20pollution%20in%20the%20community%20and%20warned%20of%20the%20potential%20consequences.%20But%20agency%20leaders%2C%20who%20answer%20to%20commissioners%20appointed%20by%20the%20governor%2C%20failed%20to%20act.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20they%20made%20the%20problem%20worse.%20The%20financial%20health%20of%20the%20state's%20oil%2C%20gas%20and%20chemical%20industries%20took%20precedence%20over%20the%20physical%20health%20of%20its%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20business-first%20philosophy%20is%20so%20ingrained%20in%20Texas%20culture%20that%20people%20who%20live%20here%20are%20clear-eyed%20about%20the%20tradeoff%2C%20even%20if%20they%20don't%20accept%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Comparing%20the%20risk%20of%20cancer%20in%20Jacintoport%20to%20the%20US%20and%20Harris%20County%2C%20Texas.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578d9ab50edbc52a8638b13%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%20Community%20Health%20News%3B%20EPA%202019%20AirToxScreen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHarris%20County%20Attorney%20Christian%20Menefee%2C%20the%20county's%20chief%20civil%20lawyer%2C%20said%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bappalled%20but%20not%20surprised%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20TCEQ's%20inaction%20in%20Channelview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20shows%20that%20the%20state%20of%20Texas%20has%20no%20meaningful%20oversight%20over%20these%20corporations.%20They're%20allowed%20to%20run%20rampant%20in%20our%20communities%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Menefee%2C%20who%20has%20used%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublichealthwatch.org%2F2022%2F06%2F02%2Fhouston-texas-air-pollution-lyondellbasell-refinery%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20county's%20limited%20authority%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20penalize%20polluters.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they%20want%20to%20pollute%20the%20air%20in%20a%20way%20that%20is%20so%20aggressive%20that%20it%20can%20cause%20people%20to%20get%20sick%20or%20get%20diseases%2C%20they're%20allowed%20to%20do%20so.%20The%20agency%20that%20has%20been%20set%20up%20by%20the%20state%20to%20come%20in%20and%20rein%20these%20folks%20in%20just%20repeatedly%20fails%20to%20do%20its%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETim%20Doty%20is%20the%20scientist%20who%20led%20the%20TCEQ%20mobile%20monitoring%20team%20that%20recorded%20Channelview's%20high%20benzene%20levels%20back%20in%202005%20and%202006.%20Now%20retired%20from%20the%20TCEQ%2C%20he%20spent%20his%20career%20hunting%20down%20emissions%20from%20oil%20refineries%20and%20chemical%20plants%20across%20Texas.%20On%20each%20trip%2C%20Doty's%20scientists%20spent%20about%20a%20week%20in%20Harris%20County%2C%20home%20to%20the%20biggest%20petrochemical%20complex%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20collecting%20readings%20outside%20multibillion-dollar%20plants%20and%20embedding%20themselves%20in%20seas%20of%20tanks%20loaded%20with%20chemicals.%20But%20it%20was%20K-Solv%2C%20an%20unassuming%20facility%20on%204%20acres%20of%20land%2C%20that%20worried%20them%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20put%20the%20worst%20offenders%20near%20the%20top%20of%20its%20post-trip%20reports%2C%20Doty%20said%2C%20and%20K-Solv%20was%20at%20or%20near%20the%20top%20of%20every%20one.%20On%20the%20team's%20first%20trip%2C%20K-Solv%20was%20listed%20above%20far%20bigger%20facilities%2C%20including%20LyondellBasell's%20nearly%204%2C000-acre%20complex%20in%20North%20Channelview%2C%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20petrochemical%20facilities%20on%20the%20Gulf%20Coast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reports%20show%20that%20one-hour%20benzene%20levels%20outside%20K-Solv%20consistently%20exceeded%20the%20TCEQ%20guidelines%20in%20place%20at%20the%20time.%20On%20one%20trip%20the%20scientists%20recorded%20a%20one-hour%20sample%20of%20180%20ppb.%20Doty%20said%20it%20was%20one%20of%20the%20highest%20benzene%20readings%20he%20had%20ever%20seen%20in%20a%20residential%20area.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoty%20remembers%20talking%20with%20a%20man%20who%20lived%20across%20the%20street%20from%20K-Solv.%20The%20man%20told%20him%20that%20clouds%20of%20chemicals%20floated%20into%20his%20home%20each%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20time%20we%20spoke%2C%20he%20seemed%20surprised%20to%20see%20me.%20He'd%20figured%20nobody%20cared%20about%20what%20was%20happening%20in%20Channelview%2C%26quot%3B%20Doty%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20what%20happened%20to%20him%2C%20but%20I%20still%20think%20about%20him%20to%20this%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tim%20Doty%2C%20a%20former%20TCEQ%20mobile%20air%20monitoring%20expert%2C%20at%20the%20industrial%20edge%20of%20River%20Terrace%20Park%20in%20Channelview%2C%20Texas.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578b28350edbc52a86368bf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETim%20Doty%2C%20a%20former%20TCEQ%20mobile%20air%20monitoring%20expert%2C%20at%20the%20industrial%20edge%20of%20River%20Terrace%20Park%20in%20Channelview%2C%20Texas.%20Doty%20documented%20high%20levels%20of%20benzene%20in%20the%20Jacintoport%20neighborhood%20nearly%2020%20years%20ago%20and%20still%20worries%20about%20the%20people%20who%20live%20there.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPublic%20Health%20Watch%20sorted%20through%20nearly%20two%20dozen%20boxes%20filled%20with%20thousands%20of%20TCEQ%20documents%2C%20obtained%20through%20public-information%20requests%2C%20to%20review%20toxicology%20memos%20and%20reports%20Doty's%20team%20filed.%20We%20contacted%2013%20of%20the%2015%20TCEQ%20officials%20whose%20names%20appear%20on%20those%20documents.%20Only%20Doty%20and%20former%20TCEQ%20Executive%20Director%20Glenn%20Shankle%2C%20who%20now%20owns%20an%20environmental-consulting%20company%2C%20agreed%20to%20be%20interviewed.%20The%20TCEQ%20denied%20Public%20Health%20Watch's%20requests%20to%20speak%20with%20interim%20director%20Kelly%20Keel%20or%20other%20agency%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20Public%20Health%20Watch%20began%20trying%20to%20contact%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fksolv.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EK-Solv%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20phone%2C%20email%20and%20in%20person%20at%20its%20office%20in%20Jacintoport.%20We%20received%20no%20response%20until%20November%2C%20when%20the%20company's%20chief%20legal%20officer%2C%20Todd%20Riddle%2C%20responded%20with%20an%20email%20calling%20Public%20Health%20Watch's%20investigation%20%26quot%3Ban%20attempt%20to%20target%20K-Solv%20Group%20specifically.%26quot%3B%20Riddle%20pointed%20to%20other%20businesses%20and%20nearby%20chemical%20barges%20as%20%26quot%3Bsources%20of%20benzene%20emissions%20in%20the%20Channelview%20area.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EK-Solv%20Group%20is%20a%20privately%20owned%20chemical-distribution%20and%20maritime-services%20company.%20Its%20main%20facility%2C%20opened%20in%202004%2C%20now%20occupies%20about%208%20acres%20along%20the%20San%20Jacinto%20River%20in%20Channelview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%2034-minute%20interview%20and%20in%20subsequent%20emails%2C%20Riddle%20refused%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20high%20benzene%20emissions%20the%20TCEQ%20had%20recorded%20outside%20K-Solv%20because%20he%20said%20he%20had%20not%20seen%20the%20TCEQ%20monitoring-trip%20and%20toxicology%20reports.%20Public%20Health%20Watch%20obtained%20those%20documents%20through%20a%20public-records%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20spend%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20annually%20to%20not%20only%20limit%20and%20prevent%20any%20harmful%20emissions%20of%20any%20substance%2C%20but%20to%20provide%20our%20workforce%2C%20our%20neighbors%20and%20community%20the%20healthiest%20facility%20we%20possibly%20can%2C%26quot%3B%20Riddle%20said%20in%20a%20written%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Christmas%20decorations%20are%20displayed%20behind%20a%20barbed-wire%20fence%20at%20K-Solv's%20office%20in%20Channelview's%20Jacintoport%20neighborhood.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578a00a0ec98e92f74e9826%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChristmas%20decorations%20are%20displayed%20behind%20a%20fence%20at%20K-Solv's%20office%20in%20Channelview's%20Jacintoport%20neighborhood.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPublic%20Health%20Watch%20interviewed%20dozens%20of%20current%20and%20former%20Channelview%20residents.%20They%20described%20their%20community's%20transformation%20from%20a%20rural%20enclave%20into%20an%20industrial%20center%20and%20from%20a%20majority-white%20to%20a%20majority-Hispanic%20community.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMany%20told%20of%20losing%20neighbors%20and%20family%20members%20to%20cancer%20and%20watching%20others%20struggle%20with%20asthma%20and%20similar%20breathing%20issues.%20Some%20were%20dealing%20with%20their%20own%20health%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFew%20spoke%20more%20passionately%20than%20the%20surviving%20members%20of%20the%20Lopez%20family%2C%20who%20lived%20across%20the%20street%20from%20K-Solv%20for%20nearly%2020%20years%20before%20evacuating%20their%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoe%20Lopez%20died%20in%202004%20of%20kidney%20failure%20triggered%20by%20diabetes%20at%20the%20age%20of%2065.%20His%20wife%2C%20Dora%2C%20overcame%20thyroid%20cancer%20but%20needed%20a%20breathing%20machine%20for%20the%20last%20years%20of%20her%20life.%20Joel%20Lopez%2C%20the%20eldest%20of%20their%20three%20sons%2C%20cared%20for%20her%20until%20she%20died%20in%202017.%20He%20has%20been%20diagnosed%20with%20myelodysplasia%2C%20a%20blood%20cancer%20that%20can%20develop%20into%20leukemia.%20He%20struggles%20with%20complications%20from%20diabetes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20try%20to%20persuade%20my%20mother%20to%20sell%20everything%20and%20just%20go%20someplace%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Randy%20Lopez%2C%20the%20middle%20son.%20He%20left%20Channelview%20when%20he%20was%20a%20teenager%20and%20is%20in%20good%20health%20today.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20a%20cancer%20was%20embedded%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20Channelview.%20It's%20just%20extremely%20depressing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Joel%20(left)%20and%20Randy%20Lopez%20at%20Joel's%20home%20in%20Houston%2C%20Texas.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578a0ac0ec98e92f74e9863%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJoel%20(left)%20and%20Randy%20Lopez%20at%20Joel's%20home%20in%20Houston%2C%20Texas.%20The%20brothers%20grew%20up%20hunting%20and%20riding%20horses%20in%20Jacintoport%2C%20but%20that%20was%20before%20industry%20overran%20the%20area%20and%20K-Solv%20opened%20across%20the%20street%20from%20their%20family%20home.%20Joel%20is%20being%20treated%20for%20myelodysplasia%2C%20a%20blood%20cancer%20that%20can%20develop%20into%20leukemia.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBenzene%20has%20been%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20the%20Texas%20economy%20since%201901%2C%20when%20wildcatters%20struck%20%26quot%3Bblack%20gold%26quot%3B%20at%20Spindletop.%20The%20oil%20boom%20transformed%20Texas%20from%20an%20agrarian%20state%20to%20one%20with%20bustling%20cities%20and%20national%20influence.%20It%20also%20birthed%20a%20class%20of%20oil%20barons%20whose%20wealth%20and%20conservative%20political%20interests%20shaped%20national%20politics%20and%20popularized%20Texas%20culture%20in%20movies%20and%20TV%20shows.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarris%20County%2C%20where%20Channelview%20is%20located%2C%20was%20the%20main%20beneficiary%20of%20this%20evolution.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20World%20War%20II%2C%20the%20county%20%E2%80%94%20which%20includes%20the%20city%20of%20Houston%20%E2%80%94%20had%20emerged%20as%20an%20international%20shipping%20hub%20and%20ground%20zero%20for%20America's%20oil%20and%20gas%20industry.%20Last%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.houstonchronicle.com%2Fbusiness%2Farticle%2F11-Houston-billionaires-make-Forbes-400-richest-17470154.php%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E11%20Houston%20billionaires%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20Forbes'%20%26quot%3B400%20Richest%20Americans%26quot%3B%20list%2C%20and%20all%20but%20three%20had%20ties%20to%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20industry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20global%20demand%20for%20plastics%20has%20grown%2C%20Texas%20also%20has%20become%20a%20hub%20for%20the%20petrochemical%20industry%2C%20which%20uses%20benzene%20in%20its%20production%20processes.%20Since%202016%2C%20eight%20petrochemical%20facilities%20have%20opened%20in%20the%20state%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foilandgaswatch.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOil%20and%20Gas%20Watch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20tracks%20the%20oil%2C%20gas%20and%20petrochemical%20industries.%20Thirty%20others%20have%20expanded%2C%20including%2011%20in%20Harris%20County.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChannelview%2C%2015%20miles%20east%20of%20downtown%20Houston%2C%20has%20been%20a%20primary%20target%20for%20industrial%20expansion.%20Until%20the%201980s%20it%20was%20a%20rural%20hideaway%20where%20people%20rode%20horses%20and%20hunted%20in%20tree-lined%20fields.%20Its%20closest%20claims%20to%20fame%20were%20a%20distant%20view%20of%20the%20battleground%20where%20Texas%20won%20its%20independence%20from%20Mexico%20and%20the%20homestead%20of%20Lorenzo%20de%20Zavala%2C%20the%20Republic%20of%20Texas'%20first%20vice%20president.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20Doty's%20team%20parked%20its%20monitoring%20vans%20outside%20K-Solv%20for%20the%20first%20time%20on%20June%204%2C%202005%2C%20de%20Zavala's%20log%20house%20had%20been%20leveled%2C%20and%20industrial%20facilities%20had%20replaced%20wooded%20prairies.%20The%20Jacintoport%20neighborhood%2C%20once%20home%20to%20doctors'%20riverside%20residences%20and%20fields%20of%20azaleas%2C%20was%20besieged%20by%20petrochemical%20companies%20fighting%20for%20waterfront%20property%20near%20the%20Houston%20Ship%20Channel%2C%20a%20critical%20artery%20in%20the%20Port%20of%20Houston.%20Barges%20loaded%20with%20chemicals%20lined%20the%20shores%20of%20the%20San%20Jacinto%20River%2C%20where%20generations%20of%20families%20once%20swam.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChannelview's%20population%20was%20changing%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20industries%20moved%20in%2C%20its%20once-overwhelmingly%20white%20population%20began%20shrinking.%20Today%20more%20than%2070%25%20of%20residents%20identify%20as%20Hispanic.%20The%20poverty%20rate%20has%20risen%20from%2015%25%20in%202005%20to%20nearly%2021%25.%20Almost%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20population%20doesn't%20have%20health%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FoNWFe%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22A%20quarter%20of%20Channelview%E2%80%99s%20residents%20are%20uninsured%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22233%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FPA3Mw%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Channelview%E2%80%99s%20demographics%20change%20as%20industries%20move%20in%20%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FvARNM%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Poverty%20gap%20widens%20in%20last%20decade%5Cn%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAlison%20Cohen%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20epidemiology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20San%20Francisco%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs10389-017-0857-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudies%20industrial%20pollution%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20communities%20around%20the%20world.%20She%20said%20this%20kind%20of%20population%20shift%20is%20common%20when%20large%20numbers%20of%20industries%20move%20into%20residential%20areas.%20People%20who%20can%20afford%20to%20move%20do.%20Those%20left%20behind%20tend%20to%20be%20poorer%20and%20have%20less%20political%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCommunities%20that%20bear%20a%20disproportionately%20high%20burden%20of%20environmental%20pollution%20tend%20to%20also%20have%20less%20access%20to%20affordable%2C%20high-quality%20health%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20Cohen%20said.%20%26quot%3BSince%20being%20exposed%20to%20higher%20levels%20of%20environmental%20pollution%20can%20have%20health%20consequences%2C%20it%20is%20particularly%20important%20that%20residents%20in%20communities%20like%20Channelview%20have%2C%20at%20a%20minimum%2C%20equal%20access%20to%20that%20kind%20of%20care.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Tim%20Doty's%20team%20began%20monitoring%20in%20Channelview%20in%202005%2C%20the%20TCEQ%20was%20under%20fire%20from%20clean-air%20advocates%20and%20then-Houston%20Mayor%20Bill%20White%2C%20who%20questioned%20the%20agency's%20commitment%20to%20policing%20industrial%20pollution%20in%20and%20around%20the%20city.%20The%20state%20needed%20to%20save%20face%2C%20and%20Glenn%20Shankle%2C%20the%20TCEQ's%20executive%20director%20at%20the%20time%2C%20wanted%20Doty's%20mobile%20monitoring%20team%20to%20get%20to%20Houston%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible.%20Shankle's%20instructions%20were%20clear%3A%20Track%20down%20any%20extreme%20benzene%20levels%20in%20the%20area.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20used%20mobile%20monitoring%20in%20what%20we%20would%20call%20'hot%20spots%2C'%26quot%3B%20Shankle%20told%20Public%20Health%20Watch.%20%26quot%3BI%20kind%20of%20took%20the%20lead%20on%20Houston%20because%20of%20all%20their%20problems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20visited%2026%20facilities%20in%20Harris%20County%20but%20quickly%20zeroed%20in%20on%20K-Solv.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20facility%2C%20less%20than%20200%20feet%20from%20the%20Lopez%20home%20and%20other%20residences%2C%20was%20a%20frenzy%20of%20activity.%20Barges%20sat%20docked%20on%20its%20backside%2C%20waiting%20for%20often-volatile%20products%20to%20be%20removed%20from%20the%20vessels'%20bottoms%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bheels.%26quot%3B%20Hoses%20carrying%20chemicals%20snaked%20to%20metal%20storage%20tanks%20or%20idling%2018-wheelers%2C%20ready%20to%20rumble%20through%20Jacintoport's%20once-quiet%20streets.%20A%20metal%20shed%20containing%20barrels%20of%20chemicals%20sat%20at%20the%20complex's%20northern%20boundary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20that%20first%20investigation%2C%20Doty's%20scientists%20conducted%20about%2080%20hours%20of%20air%20monitoring%20near%20homes%20downwind%20of%20the%20facility%2C%20according%20to%20the%20trip%20report.%20They%20used%20metal%20canisters%20to%20trap%20air%20samples%20and%2016-foot%20box%20vans%20outfitted%20with%20small%20ovens%20that%20analyzed%20real-time%20readings%20by%20burning%20off%20chemicals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20detected%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20chemicals.%20But%20benzene%20was%20their%20priority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20that%20there%20is%20no%20safe%20level%20of%20exposure%20to%20benzene%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cohen%2C%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20San%20Francisco%2C%20epidemiologist.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20that%20exposure%20to%20it%20over%20time%20may%20add%20up%20to%20increase%20the%20risk%20of%20health%20issues%20in%20both%20children%20and%20adults.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoty%20was%20accustomed%20to%20measuring%20high%20benzene%20levels%20outside%20refineries.%20But%20even%20he%20was%20shocked%20by%20what%20he%20found%20downwind%20of%20K-Solv.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20map%20of%20K-Solv%20locations%20and%20the%20Channelview%20area.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578ab060ec98e92f74e9f75%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221311%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%20Community%20Health%20News%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%2C%20the%20monitoring%20team%20recorded%20an%2018-hour%20average%20of%2023%20ppb%20of%20benzene%2C%20which%20Doty%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bfar%20more%20telling%20than%20a%20one-hour%20reading%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bbenzene%20levels%20I'd%20never%20want%20my%20family%20exposed%20to.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20also%20found%20high%20levels%20of%20propylene%20and%20butane%20%E2%80%93%20compounds%20used%20to%20make%20plastics%20that%20can%20cause%20conditions%20ranging%20from%20shortness%20of%20breath%20to%20liver%20damage.%20In%20extremely%20high%20concentrations%20they%20can%20cause%20people%20to%20pass%20out%20or%20even%20die%20from%20asphyxiation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team's%20tests%20showed%20that%20Channelview%20residents%20were%20breathing%20a%20cocktail%20of%20chemicals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20compounds%2C%20like%20benzene%2C%20whose%20sweet%20smell%20often%20goes%20unnoticed%2C%20didn't%20cause%20much%20alarm%20in%20the%20community.%20Other%20compounds%20with%20distinct%20odors%20were%20harder%20to%20ignore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20health%20consequences%20of%20exposures%20to%20mixtures%20of%20chemicals%20can%20be%20complex%2C%26quot%3B%20Cohen%20said.%20%26quot%3BEvidence%20suggests%20that%2C%20at%20minimum%2C%20the%20health%20risks%20related%20to%20each%20chemical%20exposure%20combined%20add%20up%20to%20a%20greater%20health%20risk.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20child%20on%20the%20swings%20at%20River%20Terrace%20Park%2C%20located%20a%20little%20more%20than%20a%20mile%20feet%20from%20K-Solv.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578ac1b7a3c8094d5dc2622%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERiver%20Terrace%20Park%20is%20located%20a%20little%20more%20than%20a%20mile%20from%20K-Solv.%20The%20popular%20park%20is%20even%20closer%20to%20chemical%20barges%20and%20industrial%20cranes%20along%20the%20San%20Jacinto%20River.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24213935-mobile-monitoring-report-june-2005%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20monitoring%20team's%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20sent%20to%20Michael%20Honeycutt%2C%20who%20led%20the%20TCEQ's%20toxicology%20division%20for%2020%20years.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20his%20staff%20evaluated%20monitor%20readings%20by%20comparing%20them%20with%20the%20guidelines%20used%20on%20state-issued%20permits%20to%20set%20emission%20limits%20for%20industrial%20facilities.%20Called%20effects%20screening%20levels%2C%20the%20guidelines%20were%20created%20to%20%26quot%3Bprotect%20human%20health%20and%20welfare%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tceq.texas.gov%2Ftoxicology%2Famcv%2Fabout%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20TCEQ's%20website%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEight%20of%20the%20one-hour%20samples%20Doty's%20team%20measured%20during%20that%20trip%20exceeded%20the%2025%20ppb%20permit%20guideline%20at%20the%20time.%20The%20highest%20reading%20was%20double%20that%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESenior%20toxicologist%20Valerie%20Meyers%20wrote%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24213937-toxicology-memo-june-2005%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20memo%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20response%20to%20Doty's%20report.%20Directed%20to%20the%20agency's%20top%20permitting%20and%20enforcement%20officials%2C%20it%20noted%20that%20%26quot%3Bpersistently%20elevated%20levels%20of%20benzene%20may%20contribute%20to%20long-term%20health%20concerns.%26quot%3B%C2%A0In%20a%20section%20of%20the%20memo%20labeled%20%26quot%3Bdownwind%20of%20K-Solv%2C%26quot%3B%20Meyers%20recommended%20installing%20a%20long-term%2C%20stationary%20monitor%20in%20Jacintoport%20to%20help%20the%20TCEQ%20%26quot%3Bfully%20characterize%20chronic%20exposure%20and%20risk.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team's%20report%20also%20prompted%20the%20TCEQ%20to%20launch%20an%20on-site%20investigation%20of%20K-Solv's%20operation%20in%20February%202006.%20The%20investigation%20found%20that%20the%20company%20was%20relieving%20pressure%20in%20its%20chemical%20tanks%20by%20routinely%20%26quot%3Bburping%26quot%3B%20emissions%20directly%20into%20the%20air%20instead%20of%20venting%20them%20through%20proper%20pollution%20controls.%20K-Solv%20was%20fined%20%244%2C320%20and%20ordered%20to%20install%20new%20relief%20valves%20on%20its%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mobile%20monitoring%20team%20visited%20Harris%20County%20three%20more%20times%20between%20December%202005%20and%20December%202006.%20K-Solv%20was%20a%20priority%20during%20these%20trips%2C%20Doty%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20trip%20was%20as%20revelatory%20as%20the%20one%20in%20April%202006.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%20the%20scientists%20measured%20a%20one-hour%20average%20benzene%20concentration%20of%20180%20ppb%2C%20seven%20times%20the%2025%20ppb%20limit%20at%20the%20time.%20Other%20one-hour%20readings%20were%20almost%20as%20high%3A%20170%20ppb%2C%20130%20ppb%2C%20110%20ppb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chart%20showing%20the%20level%20of%20benzene%20near%20the%20K-Solv%20facility%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578daae50edbc52a8638bba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221314%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%20Community%20Health%20News%3B%20Texas%20Commission%20on%20Environmental%20Quality%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20also%20measured%20high%20levels%20of%20other%20chemicals%2C%20including%20methyl%20t-butyl%20ether%20and%201-pentene%20%E2%80%94%20gasoline%20additives%20with%20strong%20odors%20that%20can%20burn%20the%20eyes%20and%20throat%20and%20cause%20wheezing%20and%20dizziness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoty%20had%20seen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublichealthwatch.org%2F2023%2F04%2F26%2Ftexas-houston-environment-pollution-epa-mitsui%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esimilarly%20elevated%20benzene%20levels%3C%2Fa%3E%20outside%20oil%20refineries%20and%20large%20chemical%20plants.%20But%20those%20facilities%20were%20usually%20far%20from%20populated%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20whole%20other%20level%20to%20find%20elevated%2C%20constant%20concentrations%20like%20that%20in%20a%20residential%20area%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20mean%2C%20we%20were%20literally%20across%20the%20street%20from%20residential%20houses.%20That's%20a%20whole%20different%20ball%20game.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202006%2C%20Meyers%20sent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24213936-toxicology-memo-december-2006%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanother%20internal%20memo%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Again%20she%20highlighted%20elevated%20benzene%20levels%20in%20a%20section%20of%20the%20memo%20labeled%20%26quot%3Bdownwind%20of%20K-Solv.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20some%20concern%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20measurements%2C%20she%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3Bdue%20to%20the%20proximity%20of%20the%20neighborhood%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20benzene%20is%20a%20known%20carcinogen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20row%20of%20double-wide%20homes%20in%20Channelview%2C%20Texas.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578af167a3c8094d5dc2867%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20row%20of%20double-wide%20homes%20in%20Channelview%2C%20Texas.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMeyers%20reiterated%20the%20recommendation%20she%20had%20made%20eight%20months%20earlier%3A%20a%20long-term%2C%20stationary%20monitor%20near%20K-Solv%20was%20the%20best%20way%20to%20evaluate%20the%20%26quot%3Bpotential%20human%20health%20risk%26quot%3B%20the%20company's%20emissions%20posed%20to%20residents.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20violations%20were%20issued%20to%20K-Solv.%20The%20TCEQ%20leaders%20who%20received%20the%20memo%20%E2%80%94%20Richard%20Hyde%2C%20director%20of%20the%20air%20permits%20division%2C%20and%20John%20Sadlier%2C%20then%20director%20of%20the%20enforcement%20division%20%E2%80%94%20stuck%20with%20the%20agency's%20wait-and-see%20approach.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeyers%2C%20who%20now%20works%20at%20NASA%20and%20uses%20the%20last%20name%20Ryder%2C%20declined%20to%20speak%20with%20Public%20Health%20Watch%20about%20her%20actions%20in%20response%20to%20K-Solv's%20benzene%20emissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHyde%2C%20who%20went%20on%20to%20serve%20as%20the%20TCEQ's%20executive%20director%20from%202014%20to%202018%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.transparencyusa.org%2Ftx%2Flobbying%2Flobbyist%2Frichard-a-hyde-69968%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enow%20works%20as%20a%20lobbyist%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20petrochemical%20industry.%20He%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20calls%20and%20emails%20from%20Public%20Health%20Watch.%20Sadlier%2C%20who%20worked%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftruthout.org%2Farticles%2Fexxonmobil-is-counting-on-trump-chosen-judge-to-undermine-right-to-sue-polluters%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsultant%20for%20Exxon%20Mobil%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20he%20left%20the%20TCEQ%2C%20did%20not%20respond%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%202006%2C%20the%20monitor%20that%20Meyers%20had%20recommended%20had%20been%20installed%20in%20a%20clearing%20five%20blocks%20from%20K-Solv%2C%20where%20it%20would%20be%20likely%20to%20capture%20emissions%20downwind%20from%20the%20facility.%20The%20metal%20canister%20would%20gather%2024-hour%20air%20samples%20that%20could%20be%20collected%20manually%20and%20taken%20to%20the%20TCEQ%20laboratory%20for%20analysis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20the%20automated%20gas%20chromatograph%20air%20monitor%20Doty%20had%20hoped%20for%20%E2%80%94%20a%20state-of-the-art%20instrument%20that%20could%20continuously%20feed%20air%20samples%20directly%20into%20the%20agency's%20database.%20But%20it%20still%20felt%20like%20progress.%20Doty%20believed%20his%20group%20of%20scientists%2C%20named%20the%20TCEQ's%20%26quot%3B2005%20team%20of%20the%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20had%20taken%20the%20people%20of%20Channelview%20one%20step%20closer%20to%20safety%20and%20K-Solv%20one%20step%20closer%20to%20accountability.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFew%20people%2C%20if%20any%2C%20in%20Channelview%20knew%20about%20the%20TCEQ's%20growing%20concern%20about%20high%20benzene%20levels%20outside%20K-Solv.%20That%20information%2C%20buried%20in%20stacks%20of%20TCEQ%20monitoring%20reports%20and%20memos%2C%20hadn't%20been%20shared%20with%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20afternoon%20of%20April%2019%2C%202007%2C%20however%2C%20K-Solv%20grabbed%20just%20about%20everybody's%20attention.%20A%20tanker%20truck%20at%20the%20facility%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chron.com%2Fneighborhood%2Farticle%2FExploding-tankers-cause-massive-fire-9606390.php%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewent%20up%20in%20flames%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20it%20was%20being%20loaded%20with%20xylene%2C%20a%20highly%20volatile%20liquid%20found%20in%20paint%20thinners%20and%20coatings.%20A%20plume%20of%20smoke%20shot%20into%20the%20sky%2C%20and%20ashes%20covered%20houses%20and%20cars%20with%20soot.%20Fire%20engines%20raced%20through%20the%20community's%20narrow%20streets.%20A%20K-Solv%20worker%20was%20rushed%20to%20the%20hospital%20with%20third-degree%20burns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoel%20Lopez%2C%20the%20oldest%20son%20in%20the%20family%20that%20lived%20across%20the%20street%20from%20K-Solv%2C%20was%20at%20work%20when%20he%20got%20a%20desperate%20phone%20call%20from%20his%20mother.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20mom%20was%20scared.%20It%20was%20really%2C%20really%20bad%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BShe%20had%20to%20evacuate%20the%20area%20because%20of%20the%20toxic%20fumes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fire%20lasted%20roughly%20an%20hour%2C%20but%20chemicals%20leaked%20into%20the%20community%20for%2026%20more%20hours%2C%20according%20to%20TCEQ%20reports.%20The%20reports%20said%20the%20accident%20released%20about%203%2C000%20pounds%20of%20xylene%2C%20which%20can%20cause%20headaches%20and%20irritate%20the%20eyes%2C%20nose%20and%20throat%2C%20and%20240%20pounds%20of%20carbon%20monoxide%2C%20which%20can%20cause%20fatigue%20and%20confusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRight%20now%2C%20our%20main%20concern%20is%20the%20safety%20of%20our%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20K-Solv%20owner%20Russell%20Allen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chron.com%2Fneighborhood%2Farticle%2FExploding-tankers-cause-massive-fire-9606390.php%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20reporters%20at%20the%20time.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20has%20been%20contained%20and%20no%20contaminants%20went%20into%20the%20river.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20TCEQ%20cited%20K-Solv%20for%20two%20violations%20related%20to%20the%20fire%20and%20told%20them%20to%20fix%20the%20problems.%20But%20the%20agency%20didn't%20fine%20or%20otherwise%20penalize%20K-Solv.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20agency%20rarely%20fines%20companies%20that%20violate%20Texas%20air%20pollution%20laws.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenvironmentalintegrity.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F02%2FBreakdowns-in-Enforcement-Report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20nonprofit%20advocacy%20groups%20Environment%20Texas%20and%20the%20Environmental%20Integrity%20Project%2C%20polluters%20in%20Texas%20were%C2%A0fined%20for%20less%20than%203%25%20of%20the%20nearly%2025%2C000%20illegal%20releases%C2%A0between%202011%20and%202016.%20A%20TCEQ%20spokesperson%20disputed%20those%20findings%2C%20telling%20Public%20Health%20Watch%20last%20year%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20current%20enforcement%20rate%20for%20reported%20emission%20events%20is%20more%20than%2010%25.%26quot%3B%20The%20TCEQ%20did%20not%20respond%20when%20asked%20if%20that%20number%20still%20stands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tim%20Doty%20uses%20an%20infrared%20camera%20to%20observe%20emissions%20from%20K-Solv's%20Jacintoport%20facility.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578b06e7a3c8094d5dc28f3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETim%20Doty%20uses%20an%20infrared%20camera%20to%20observe%20emissions%20from%20K-Solv's%20Jacintoport%20facility%20on%20August%2028%2C%202023.%20The%20former%20TCEQ%20air%20monitoring%20expert%20said%20the%20chemical%20distribution%20site%20has%20grown%20significantly%20since%20he%20first%20documented%20high%20levels%20of%20benzene%20and%20other%20pollutants%20there%20in%202005.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20punishing%20violators%20with%20fines%2C%20the%20TCEQ%20usually%20encourages%20them%20to%20make%20voluntary%20fixes%20or%20allows%20them%20to%20use%20the%20state's%20%26quot%3Baffirmative-defense%26quot%3B%20rule.%20It%20enables%20polluters%20to%20avoid%20being%20penalized%20if%20they%20file%20a%20written%20report%20describing%20how%20an%20incident%20was%20%26quot%3Bunavoidable%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bbeyond%20the%20control%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20months%20after%20the%20fire%2C%20the%20results%20from%20Doty's%20fourth%20trip%20to%20Channelview%20were%20circulated%20among%20TCEQ%20leaders.%20Again%2C%20his%20team%20had%20documented%20benzene%20levels%20near%20K-Solv%20that%20exceeded%20state%20guidelines%2C%20including%20a%20one-hour%20reading%20of%2052%20ppb%2C%20more%20than%20double%20the%2025%20ppb%20Texas%20considered%20acceptable%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20also%20reported%20that%20readings%20of%20two%20other%20chemicals%20outside%20K-Solv%20exceeded%20state%20guidelines.%20Styrene%2C%20a%20compound%20used%20in%20latex%2C%20can%20cause%20people%20to%20feel%20drunk%20and%20experience%20color%20changes%20in%20their%20vision.%20Methyl%20ethyl%20ketone%2C%20a%20solvent%20found%20in%20lacquers%20and%20varnishes%2C%20can%20cause%20dizziness%20and%20vomiting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202007%2C%20the%20TCEQ%20toxicology%20department%20responded%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24213938-toxicology-memo-september-2007%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20interoffice%20memo%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Matt%20Baker%2C%20the%20new%20director%20of%20enforcement%2C%20and%20other%20agency%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20emissions%20the%20team%20found%20were%20not%20%26quot%3Bexpected%20to%20cause%20short-term%20health%20effects%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20memo%20said%20in%20a%20section%20titled%20%26quot%3BJacintoport%20Neighborhood%20Area.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%20section%20titled%20%26quot%3BDownwind%20of%20K-Solv%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added%20that%20long-term%20monitoring%20from%20the%20metal%20canister%20the%20TCEQ%20had%20installed%20a%20year%20earlier%20would%20help%20the%20agency%20%26quot%3Bmore%20fully%20evaluate%20long-term%20benzene%20levels%20and%20potential%20human%20health%20risk.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20weeks%20after%20the%20memo%20was%20sent%2C%20the%20TCEQ%20did%20what%20the%20agency%20describes%20as%20routine%20air%20reconnaissance%20in%20Jacintoport%20%E2%80%94%20the%20type%20of%20monitoring%20it%20often%20does%20to%20check%20for%20obvious%20chemical%20emissions%20in%20industrialized%20areas.%20The%20process%20is%20quick%20and%20cheap.%20Investigators%20typically%20pace%20the%20streets%20near%20industrial%20facilities%20and%20use%20infrared%20cameras%20to%20search%20for%20visible%20emissions%20and%20their%20noses%20to%20check%20for%20odors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20row%20of%20tanks%20looms%20above%20an%20office%20building%20at%20K-Solv's%20chemical%20distribution%20facility.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578b1377a3c8094d5dc2969%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20row%20of%20tanks%20looms%20above%20an%20office%20building%20at%20K-Solv's%20chemical%20distribution%20facility.%20Since%202005%2C%20two%20large%20fires%20have%20broken%20out%20at%20the%20facility%20and%20the%20TCEQ%20has%20documented%20high%20benzene%20levels%20downwind%20of%20it.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20report%20filed%20by%20the%20two%20investigators%20sent%20to%20Jacintoport%20said%20they%20smelled%20an%20odor%20outside%20K-Solv.%20According%20to%20their%20report%2C%20K-Solv's%20workers%20spotted%20them%2C%20and%20suddenly%20the%20odor%20went%20away.%20The%20investigators%20said%20they%20ducked%20out%20of%20sight%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20odor%20immediately%20returned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20inspectors%20returned%20to%20K-Solv%20a%20few%20days%20later%20and%20filed%20another%20report%20saying%20the%20same%20thing%20had%20happened.%20In%20both%20reports%20the%20inspectors%20said%20the%20chemical%20odor%20was%20so%20strong%20that%20they%20left%20with%20headaches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20incident%20was%20considered%20a%20violation%20of%20TCEQ%20rules%2C%20and%20no%20enforcement%20action%20was%20taken.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EK-Solv's%20lawyer%2C%20Todd%20Riddle%2C%20declined%20to%20answer%20questions%20about%20these%20incidents%20because%2C%20he%20said%2C%20he%20hadn't%20seen%20these%20reports%2C%20which%20are%20available%20to%20the%20public.%20Instead%2C%20he%20asked%20if%20Public%20Health%20Watch%20had%20%26quot%3Bany%20more%20information%20or%20documentation%20about%20such%20conduct%20lately.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20at%20about%20this%20time%20that%20Texas%20took%20the%20unusual%20step%20of%20weakening%20its%20permit%20guidelines%20for%20benzene%20and%20six%20other%20toxic%20chemicals.%20The%20move%20was%20part%20of%20a%20years-long%20campaign%20led%20by%20the%20TCEQ's%20lead%20toxicologist%2C%20Michael%20Honeycutt%2C%20who%20was%20known%20for%20his%20strong%20opposition%20to%20regulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20one-hour%20permit%20guideline%20was%20increased%20to%2053%20ppb%2C%20more%20than%20double%20what%20the%20agency%20said%20was%20permissible%20in%202005%20and%20almost%20seven%20times%20as%20much%20as%20what%20California%20says%20is%20safe.%20Texas%20also%20increased%20its%20annual%20guideline%20from%201%20ppb%20to%201.4%20ppb.%20That's%20more%20than%20three%20times%20weaker%20than%20Maine's%2C%20the%20second-most%20lenient%20annual%20guideline%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELoren%20Hopkins%2C%20Alison%20Cohen%20and%20Cloelle%20Danforth%20%E2%80%94%20the%20three%20scientists%20who%20analyzed%20the%20TCEQ's%20Channelview%20monitoring%20data%20for%20Public%20Health%20Watch%20%E2%80%94%20said%20it's%20extremely%20rare%20for%20U.S.%20regulatory%20agencies%20to%20relax%20their%20exposure%20limits%20for%20toxic%20chemicals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Danforth%20was%20a%20senior%20scientist%20with%20the%20Environmental%20Defense%20Fund%2C%20she%20and%20Hopkins%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsetac.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1002%2Fieam.4814%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eco-authored%20a%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20provided%20a%20road%20map%20for%20responding%20to%20high%20ambient%20benzene%20levels%20during%20chemical%20disasters.%20Published%20this%20year%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20Integrated%20Environmental%20Assessment%20and%20Management%2C%20it%20suggested%20more%20stringent%20and%20precise%20benzene%20guidelines%20than%20what%20are%20currently%20in%20place%20in%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Loren%20Hopkins%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Rice%20University%20and%20a%20nationally%20recognized%20expert%20in%20environmental%20science.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578b1fe7a3c8094d5dc2a5f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELoren%20Hopkins%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Rice%20University%20and%20a%20nationally%20recognized%20expert%20in%20environmental%20science.%20Hopkins%20said%20benzene%20levels%20in%20Channelview%20are%20higher%20than%20anywhere%20else%20in%20the%20Houston%20region.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EHoneycutt's%20toxicology%20division%20soon%20took%20an%20even%20more%20dramatic%20step%20to%20weaken%20Texas'%20benzene%20guidelines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20using%20permit%20guidelines%20to%20assess%20health%20risks%20for%20residents%2C%20in%20October%202007%20his%20division%20created%20a%20new%20one-hour%20guideline%20for%20the%20toxicologists%20to%20use.%20Called%20the%20%26quot%3BAmbient%20Monitoring%20Comparison%20Value%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20was%20set%20at%20180%20ppb%20%E2%80%94%20three%20times%20higher%20than%20the%20already-weakened%20permit%20guideline%20of%2053%20ppb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20180-ppb%20limit%20is%20%26quot%3Bjust%20nuts%2C%20basically%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Eric%20Schaeffer%2C%20a%20former%20director%20of%20the%20EPA's%20Office%20of%20Civil%20Enforcement%20who%20is%20now%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Environmental%20Integrity%20Project.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20way%20out%20there.%20I%20don't%20know%20where%20they%20got%20that%20from%20and%20why%20it%20would%20be%20particularly%20credible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchaeffer%20worries%20that%20raising%20the%20limit%20provides%20a%20false%20sense%20of%20security%20for%20residents%20of%20Channelview%20and%20other%20industrialized%20communities%20in%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20question%20isn't%20whether%20there%20was%20an%20hour%20where%20%5Bbenzene%20levels%5D%20hit%20180.%20The%20question%20is%20whether%20people%20were%20exposed%20to%20much%20lower%20levels%20for%20longer%20periods%20of%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20His%20concern%20is%20that%20the%20TCEQ%20could%20%26quot%3Bgo%20out%20and%20say%2C%20'It's%20below%20180%20ppb%2C%20so%20we're%20good.'%20But%20they're%20not.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEnvironmental%20advocates%20already%20viewed%20Honeycutt%20as%20being%20too%20friendly%20toward%20industry.%20His%20move%20to%20weaken%20the%20permit%20guidelines%20reinforced%20their%20opinion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJim%20Tarr%2C%20a%20chemical%20engineer%20who%20worked%20for%20the%20TCEQ's%20predecessor%20agency%20in%20the%201970s%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublicintegrity.org%2Fenvironment%2Ftexas-weakens-chemical-exposure-guidelines-opens-door-for-polluters%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20reporter%20that%20Honeycutt's%20decision%20to%20weaken%20the%20agency's%20permit%20guideline%20for%20benzene%20was%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20irresponsible%20action%20I've%20heard%20of%20in%20my%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Doty%2C%20weakening%20the%20permit%20guidelines%20for%20polluters%20was%20akin%20to%20raising%20the%20speed%20limit%20for%20motorists.%20He%20saw%20his%20team's%20work%20in%20the%20field%20as%20more%20important%20than%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%202008%2C%20an%20energy%20boom%20took%20hold%20in%20Texas%20and%20upended%20Doty's%20team.%20A%20process%20known%20as%20hydraulic%20fracturing%2C%20or%20fracking%2C%20made%20extracting%20deeply%20buried%20deposits%20of%20oil%20and%20natural%20gas%20financially%20feasible.%20The%20process%20also%20released%20benzene%20and%20other%20naturally%20occurring%20compounds%20into%20the%20air%20and%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20air%20monitor%20installed%20by%20a%20nonprofit.%20This%20PurpleAir%20monitor%2C%20located%20at%20Carolyn%20Stone's%20home%2C%20provides%20residents%20with%20real-time%20information%20about%20potentially%20harmful%20substances%20they%20are%20breathing.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578b5d70ec98e92f74ea671%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAs%20industrial%20facilities%20have%20moved%20into%20Channelview%20and%20residents%20have%20lost%20faith%20in%20the%20TCEQ%2C%20nonprofits%20like%20Air%20Alliance%20Houston%20have%20started%20installing%20air%20monitors%20at%20homes%20to%20track%20pollution.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFracking%20turned%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rrc.texas.gov%2Foil-and-gas%2Fmajor-oil-and-gas-formations%2Fbarnett-shale%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Barnett%20Shale%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%205%2C000-square-mile%20geological%20formation%20that%20stretched%20west%20and%20south%20from%20Dallas%2C%20into%20one%20of%20the%20nation's%20largest%20onshore%20natural%20gas%20fields.%20It%20also%20represented%20a%20lifeline%20for%20state%20leaders%20desperate%20to%20stave%20off%20rising%20economic%20pressures%20from%20the%20Great%20Recession.%20The%20financial%20crisis%20was%20in%20full%20tilt%2C%20and%20the%20TCEQ%20was%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20widespread%20cuts%20that%20would%20reduce%20its%20budget%20by%2030%25%20over%20the%20next%20six%20years.%20Clamping%20down%20on%20benzene%20emissions%20could%20jeopardize%20the%20state's%20emerging%20cash%20cow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETensions%20were%20high%20at%20the%20TCEQ.%20Its%20mission%20is%20to%20protect%20public%20health%20so%20long%20as%20it%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tceq.texas.gov%2Fagency%2Fmission.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Texas%2520Commission%2520on%2520Environmental%2Cthe%2520safe%2520management%2520of%2520waste.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bconsistent%20with%20sustainable%20economic%20development.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGlenn%20Shankle%20%E2%80%94%20who%20held%20the%20executive%20director's%20job%20from%202004%20to%202008%20%E2%80%94%20said%20the%20staff%20of%20Rick%20Perry%2C%20a%20Republican%20who%20served%20as%20Texas%20governor%20from%202000%20to%202015%2C%20sometimes%20called%20his%20office%20to%20question%20the%20agency's%20enforcement%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerry%20%26quot%3Bwould%20kind%20of%20stay%20in%20our%20business%20a%20lot%2C%20I'll%20put%20it%20that%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Shankle%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.texasobserver.org%2Feven-mafia-circumspect%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleft%20the%20agency%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20job%20at%20a%20radioactive-waste%20company.%20%26quot%3BHe%20wouldn't%20call%20personally.%20He'd%20have%20a%20staff%20person%20call%20and%20go%2C%20'I%20understand%20y'all%20are%20getting%20ready%20to%20take%20enforcement%20action.%20%E2%80%A6%20Well%2C%20y'all%20might%20want%20to%20take%20another%20look%20at%20that.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoty's%20monitoring%20team%20felt%20the%20shift%20in%20the%20agency's%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20hunting%20down%20polluters%20and%20kicking%20ass%20before%20the%20fracking%20began.%20It%20really%20was%20a%20golden%20era%20for%20monitoring%2C%26quot%3B%20Doty%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20everything%20steadily%20began%20to%20change%20from%20there.%20The%20TCEQ%20leadership's%20change%20in%20strategy%20was%20obvious%3A%20The%20less%20we%20were%20allowed%20to%20look%20for%20emissions%2C%20the%20less%20we'd%20find%20problems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerry%20and%20companies%20he%20is%20affiliated%20with%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20calls%2C%20emails%20and%20Instagram%20messages%20from%20Public%20Health%20Watch.%20The%20TCEQ%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20Shankle's%20or%20Doty's%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202009%2C%20Tim%20Doty's%20team%20was%20sent%20to%20investigate%20complaints%20about%20benzene%20emissions%20from%20fracking%20operations%20in%20and%20around%20Fort%20Worth%2C%20the%20state's%20fifth-largest%20city.%20Some%20of%20the%20operations%20were%20in%20residential%20neighborhoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoty%20said%20his%20scientists%20followed%20the%20procedures%20they%20used%20for%20all%20their%20trips.%20They%20took%20quick%2C%20preliminary%20readings%2C%20then%20used%20more%20sophisticated%20equipment%20to%20collect%20air%20samples%20that%20would%20be%20tested%20in%20the%20agency's%20laboratory.%20Both%20sets%20of%20data%20would%20appear%20in%20their%20final%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20it%20was%20cold%20outside%2C%20Doty%20said%20any%20benzene%20in%20the%20air%20would%20be%20less%20active%20and%20less%20detectable%2C%20so%20he%20wasn't%20surprised%20when%20the%20preliminary%20readings%20showed%20only%20trace%20amounts.%20He%20was%20eager%20to%20see%20the%20more%20precise%20canister%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Doty%20said%20TCEQ%20field%20operations%20managers%20told%20him%20that%20additional%20analysis%20%E2%80%94%20including%20sending%20the%20more%20precise%20air%20samples%20to%20the%20lab%20%E2%80%94%20wasn't%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20had%20never%20happened%20in%20the%20history%20of%20the%20mobile%20monitoring%20team%2C%26quot%3B%20Doty%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20just%20pick%20and%20choose%20the%20samples%20you%20want%20to%20report.%20You%20have%20to%20report%20them%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Jan.%2012%2C%202010%2C%20the%20TCEQ's%20deputy%20director%20of%20compliance%20and%20enforcement%2C%20John%20Sadlier%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.texasobserver.org%2Fagency-of-destruction%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaddressed%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20Fort%20Worth%20City%20Council%20meeting%20packed%20with%20residents%20and%20clean-air%20advocates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverything%20you%20hear%20today%20will%20be%20good%20news%2C%26quot%3B%20Sadlier%20told%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20assured%20them%20that%20the%20TCEQ's%20mobile%20monitoring%20team%20had%20found%20no%20evidence%20of%20unsafe%20levels%20of%20benzene%20or%20other%20cancer-causing%20chemicals%20during%20its%20December%20trip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBased%20on%20this%20study%2C%20the%20air%20is%20safe%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20couple%20of%20weeks%20later%2C%20news%20leaked%20out%20that%20Sadlier's%20statement%20had%20been%20based%20on%20incomplete%20information.%20The%20agency's%20chief%20auditor%20opened%20a%20fraud%20investigation%20into%20the%20incident%20and%20interviewed%20eight%20people%2C%20including%20two%20managers%20in%20the%20agency's%20Field%20Operation%20Support%20division%3A%20David%20Bower%20and%20Matt%20Baker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24213933-auditors-report%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eauditor's%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20while%20the%20information%20presented%20at%20the%20council%20meeting%20was%20%26quot%3Btechnically%20accurate%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20%26quot%3Bcould%20be%20considered%20to%20be%20misleading.%26quot%3B%20But%20it%20found%20no%20evidence%20that%20management%20was%20aware%20the%20information%20%26quot%3Bcould%20be%20misleading%20at%20the%20time%20it%20was%20presented%26quot%3B%20to%20Sadlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20revealed%20that%20after%20the%20agency's%20misstep%20became%20public%2C%20the%20TCEQ%20did%20more%20monitoring%20in%20the%20Fort%20Worth%20area.%20It%20found%20that%20benzene%20levels%20there%20did%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20exceed%20the%20TCEQ's%20annual%20guideline%20of%201.4%20ppb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBaker%2C%20now%20a%20city%20council%20member%20in%20the%20Austin%20suburb%20of%20Round%20Rock%2C%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20calls%20and%20emails%20from%20Public%20Health%20Watch.%20The%20TCEQ%20did%20not%20allow%20Bower%2C%20now%20a%20special%20assistant%20in%20the%20agency's%20office%20of%20compliance%20and%20enforcement%2C%20to%20answer%20questions.%20Instead%2C%20the%20agency%20sent%20the%20following%20statement%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20assert%20that%20Mr.%20Bower%20blocked%20efforts%20to%20send%20mobile%20monitoring%20findings%20to%20the%20agency's%20laboratory%20is%20false.%20TCEQ%20strives%20to%20provide%20the%20best%20service%20to%20the%20state%20of%20Texas%20and%20any%20statement%20suggesting%20otherwise%20is%20unfounded.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Representative%20Michael%20Burgess%2C%20a%20Dallas-area%20Republican%2C%20called%20for%20then-Texas%20Attorney%20General%20Greg%20Abbott%20to%20conduct%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.texasobserver.org%2Ftceq-under-scrutiny-following-observer-story%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Brobust%20investigation%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20the%20TCEQ's%20handling%20of%20the%20matter.%20But%20Abbott%2C%20now%20the%20Republican%20governor%20of%20Texas%2C%20didn't%20open%20an%20investigation.%20He%20did%2C%20however%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.texastribune.org%2F2017%2F01%2F17%2Ftexas-federal-government-lawsuits%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esue%20the%20EPA%3C%2Fa%3E%20nine%20times%20in%202010%20for%20%26quot%3Bunlawfully%20commandeering%20Texas'%20environmental%20enforcement%20program.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20no%20fishing%20sign%20on%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20San%20Jacinto%20River.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578b6ce0ec98e92f74ea71a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGenerations%20of%20Channelview%20families%20once%20swam%20and%20fished%20in%20the%20San%20Jacinto%20River.%20But%20its%20waters%20are%20no%20longer%20considered%20safe%20because%20of%20heavy%20pollution%20from%20petrochemical%20barge%20activity.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20TCEQ%20was%20finalizing%20K-Solv's%20request%20to%20significantly%20expand%20its%20operation%20in%20Channelview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20investigators%20who%20reviewed%20the%20permit%20application%20noted%20K-Solv's%20proximity%20to%20residences%20and%20the%20history%20of%20odors%20they%20had%20documented%20outside%20the%20facility.%20They%20warned%20that%20the%20expansion%20could%20become%20%26quot%3Banother%20contributing%20factor%26quot%3B%20to%20chemical%20exposure%20in%20the%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20managers%20dismissed%20their%20concerns%2C%20and%20the%20permit%20was%20issued%20in%20February%202010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EK-Solv%20was%20allowed%20to%20legally%20increase%20its%20annual%20VOC%20emissions%20by%20299%25%3A%20from%201%2C980%20pounds%20a%20year%20to%207%2C900%20pounds%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%20two%20years%2C%20Doty's%20team%20was%20gradually%20reduced%20in%20size%20and%20stripped%20of%20its%20power%20to%20proactively%20track%20down%20polluters.%20The%20TCEQ%20stopped%20conducting%20in-depth%2C%20days-long%20monitoring%20outside%20industrial%20facilities%2C%20including%20K-Solv%2C%20in%20favor%20of%20faster%20and%20cheaper%20%26quot%3Broutine%20air%20reconnaissance.%26quot%3B%20The%20visits%20were%20usually%20brief%2C%20according%20to%20four%20TCEQ%20reports%20filed%20between%20March%202011%20and%20October%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2016%2C%202011%2C%20an%20investigator%20spent%20seven%20minutes%20outside%20K-Solv.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Aug.%2012%2C%202011%2C%20an%20investigator%20spent%2010%20minutes%20outside%20K-Solv.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2013%2C%202012%2C%20two%20investigators%20spent%2015%20minutes%20outside%20K-Solv.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Oct.%201%2C%202012%2C%20an%20investigator%20spent%20three%20minutes%20outside%20K-Solv.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reports%20said%20the%20investigators%20didn't%20see%20or%20smell%20anything%20that%20worried%20them%20during%20the%20visits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Jacintoport's%20benzene%20problem%20hadn't%20gone%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%202013%20to%202014%2C%20the%20neighborhood's%20annual%20benzene%20levels%20hovered%20around%201%20ppb%2C%20according%20to%20readings%20from%20the%20stationary%20metal%20canister%20that%20had%20been%20installed%20downwind%20of%20K-Solv.%20Annual%20readings%20that%20high%20would%20have%20set%20off%20alarm%20bells%20had%20they%20been%20taken%20in%20California%2C%20where%20the%20guideline%20is%200.1%20ppb%2C%20or%20in%20Minnesota%2C%20which%20has%20established%20a%20guideline%20of%200.24%20ppb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FNSOwT%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Texas%20has%20weakest%20annual%20benzene%20guideline%20in%20the%20country%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22420%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20the%20state%20of%20Texas%20developed%20their%20own%20toxicological%20parameters%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20United%20States%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20what%20really%20frustrates%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Loren%20Hopkins%2C%20the%20Rice%20University%20professor%2C%20when%20comparing%20Texas%20to%20the%20other%20seven%20states%20that%20have%20established%20benzene%20guidelines.%20%26quot%3BUnder%20this%20system%2C%20benzene%20has%20one%20toxicity%20factor%20here%20and%20a%20completely%20different%20one%20when%20you%20cross%20the%20border%20into%20another%20state.%20It%20doesn't%20make%20sense%20to%20me%2C%20and%20it%20never%20will.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Honeycutt%2C%20the%20Texas%20toxicologist%20who%20led%20the%20effort%20to%20weaken%20the%20TCEQ's%20chemical%20guidelines%2C%20already%20had%20a%20reputation%20for%20bucking%20widely%20accepted%20scientific%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20dog%20lies%20on%20the%20porch%20of%20a%20home%20roughly%20a%20mile%20from%20K-Solv's%20Jacintoport%20facility.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578b7710ec98e92f74ea762%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20dog%20lies%20on%20the%20porch%20of%20a%20home%20roughly%20a%20mile%20from%20K-Solv's%20Jacintoport%20facility.%20TCEQ%20data%20shows%20that%20the%20area%20has%20been%20exposed%20to%20a%20cocktail%20of%20airborne%20chemicals%20for%20nearly%20two%20decades.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202011%2C%20Honeycutt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frepublicans-science.house.gov%2F_cache%2Ffiles%2F3%2F0%2F30ede8a4-951f-4f5b-bffa-fc5ac8afb6a4%2F71262E7A7C1A2A0BD072FFDE7446189F.100411-honeycutt.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20a%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Congress%20arguing%20that%20the%20EPA%20was%20too%20stringent%20in%20its%20efforts%20to%20protect%20people%20from%20mercury%2C%20a%20toxin%20that%20can%20cause%20lung%20damage%2C%20brain%20damage%20and%20is%20especially%20dangerous%20for%20fetuses.%20%26quot%3BEPA%20ignores%20the%20fact%20that%20Japanese%20eat%2010%20times%20more%20fish%20than%20Americans%20do%20and%20have%20higher%20levels%20in%20their%20blood%20but%20have%20lower%20rates%20of%20coronary%20heart%20disease%20and%20high%20scores%20on%20their%20IQ%20tests%2C%26quot%3B%20Honeycutt%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20he%20criticized%20the%20EPA's%20efforts%20to%20regulate%20ozone%2C%20an%20odorless%2C%20colorless%20ingredient%20in%20smog%20that%20exacerbates%20asthma.%20%26quot%3BI%20haven't%20seen%20the%20data%20that%20says%20lowering%20ozone%20will%20produce%20a%20health%20benefit%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.texastribune.org%2F2014%2F10%2F21%2Fbattle-over-science-ozone-pollution%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20Texas%20Tribune.%20%26quot%3BIn%20fact%2C%20I've%20seen%20data%20that%20shows%20it%20might%20have%20a%20negative%20health%20benefit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoneycutt%20doubled%20down%20on%20that%20claim%20a%20year%20later%2C%20warning%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Fsections%2Fthetwo-way%2F2018%2F02%2F14%2F583972957%2Ftop-epa-science-adviser-has-history-of-questioning-pollution-research%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bpeople%20are%20going%20to%20die%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20the%20EPA's%20proposed%20ozone%20standards%20went%20into%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoneycutt%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20calls%20and%20emails%20from%20Public%20Health%20Watch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202016%2C%20Joel%20and%20Randy%20Lopez%20had%20persuaded%20their%2076-year-old%20mother%2C%20Dora%2C%20to%20leave%20Channelview%20for%20good.%20She%20needed%20a%20breathing%20machine%20to%20sleep%20at%20night%2C%20and%20the%20constant%20flow%20of%20chemicals%20had%20become%20unbearable%20for%20her.%20Joel%2C%20her%20primary%20caregiver%2C%20had%20done%20everything%20he%20could%20to%20protect%20her%2C%20including%20taping%20her%20windows%20and%20doors%20shut.%20But%20the%20fumes%20kept%20coming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lush%20property%20the%20Lopez%20brothers%20remembered%20from%20their%20childhood%20was%20gone.%20The%20vegetation%20had%20withered%20away%20as%20the%20pollution%20worsened%2C%20Randy%20said%2C%20leaving%20behind%20%26quot%3Ban%20empty%20wasteland%26quot%3B%20where%20nothing%20could%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoel%20Lopez%20said%20they%20sold%20the%20family%20home%20to%20K-Solv%20so%20they%20could%20pay%20for%20their%20mother's%20rising%20health%20care%20costs.%20K-Solv%20used%20the%20land%20to%20build%20an%20employee%20parking%20lot%20and%20storage%20shed%20next%20to%20its%20office%20building%2C%20part%20of%20another%20expansion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20that%20time%2C%20the%20TCEQ%20amended%20K-Solv's%20permit%20and%20allowed%20it%20to%20handle%20more%20chemicals%20and%20release%20more%20volatile%20organic%20compounds%20per%20hour%20than%20ever%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20TCEQ%20official%20who%20reviewed%20K-Solv's%20amendment%20application%20said%20in%20an%20interoffice%20memo%20that%20K-Solv%20was%20predicted%20to%20exceed%20the%20one-hour%20permit%20guideline%20for%20benzene%20%E2%80%94%20which%20they%20had%20changed%20from%2053%20ppb%20to%2054%20ppb%20%E2%80%94%20for%2054%20hours%20a%20year.%20But%20because%20that%20prediction%20was%20based%20on%20%26quot%3Bworst%20case%26quot%3B%20assumptions%2C%20the%20official%20said%20the%20agency%20did%20not%20%26quot%3Banticipate%20adverse%20health%20effects%20to%20occur%20among%20the%20general%20public.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20aerial%20view%20of%20Channelview's%20Jacintoport%20neighborhood%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65791cdd50edbc52a8639801%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22360%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChannelview's%20Jacintoport%20neighborhood%20has%20changed%20dramatically%20since%20the%201980s%20when%20industry%20began%20moving%20in.%20K-Solv%20is%20in%20the%20bottom%20right%20hand%20corner.%3Cp%3EGoogle%20Earth%3B%20Landsat%2FCopernicus%2C%20Houston-Galveston%20Area%20Council%3B%20Data%20SIO%3B%20Texas%20General%20Land%20Office%3B%20U.S.%20Geological%20Survey%3B%20National%20Oceanic%20and%20Atmospheric%20Administration%3B%20U.S.%20Navy%3B%20Geospatial-Intelligence%20Agency%3B%20General%20Bathymetric%20Chart%20of%20the%20Oceans%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20U.S.%20Environmental%20Protection%20Agency%20fined%20K-Solv%20twice%20in%20nine%20months%20%E2%80%94%20%2451%2C000%20in%20September%202015%20for%20violations%20including%20its%20failure%20to%20properly%20vent%20its%20stored%20acetic%20acid%20and%20%2450%2C000%20in%20June%202016%20for%20failing%20to%20submit%20years%20of%20federal%20paperwork%20detailing%20the%20amounts%20of%20hazardous%20chemicals%20it%20stored%20on%20its%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20point%20the%20TCEQ%20had%20fined%20K-Solv%20only%20once%20since%20the%20facility%20opened%20in%202004%3A%20%244%2C320%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Bburping%26quot%3B%20incident%20in%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20more%20industries%20were%20moving%20into%20Jacintoport%20and%20benzene%20emissions%20were%20rising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20the%20TCEQ's%20stationary%20canister%20show%20that%20from%202019%20to%20the%20beginning%20of%202021%2C%20annual%20benzene%20readings%20climbed%20well%20beyond%20the%20agency's%201.4%20ppb%20guideline.%20On%20Feb.%2011%2C%202021%2C%20the%20canister%20registered%20an%20annual%20average%20benzene%20level%20of%202.1%20ppb%20over%20the%20previous%2012%20months.%20That's%20nearly%2050%25%20above%20Texas'%20annual%20benzene%20exposure%20guideline%20and%20more%20than%2020%20times%20higher%20than%20California's%20guideline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20days%20after%20that%20reading%20was%20taken%2C%20the%20TCEQ%20replaced%20the%20canister%20with%20an%20automated%20gas%20chromatograph%2C%20the%20more%20sophisticated%20instrument%20that%20Doty%20had%20hoped%20to%20see%20installed%20more%20than%2015%20years%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20upgrade%20came%20with%20a%20catch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20old%20monitor%20was%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20Jacintoport%20neighborhood%20and%20downwind%20of%20K-Solv%2C%20the%20new%20monitor%20was%20installed%20on%20the%20northwestern%20outskirts%20of%20the%20community%20and%20farther%20from%20most%20residents'%20homes%20%E2%80%94%20a%20location%20less%20likely%20to%20pick%20up%20emissions%20from%20K-Solv%20and%20other%20companies'%20chemical-laden%20barges%20along%20the%20nearby%20riverbank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20TCEQ%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20site%20of%20the%20monitor%20was%20changed%20because%20the%20old%20site%20was%20too%20small%20to%20accommodate%20the%20new%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20implications%20of%20this%20decision%20were%20felt%20in%20April%202021%2C%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.click2houston.com%2Fvideo%2Fnews%2F2021%2F04%2F07%2Ffire-burning-at-k-solv-chemical-facility-%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflames%20spread%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20K-Solv's%20chemical%20storage%20area.%20The%20fire%20burned%20for%20nearly%20three%20hours%20and%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.tceq.texas.gov%2Foce%2Feer%2Findex.cfm%3Ffuseaction%3Dmain.getDetails%26target%3D354013%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETCEQ%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20released%20more%20than%20160%2C000%20pounds%20of%20volatile%20organic%20compounds%2C%20including%201%2C200%20pounds%20of%20toluene%2C%20which%20can%20cause%20euphoria%2C%20dilated%20pupils%20and%20nerve%20damage%2C%20and%202%2C000%20pounds%20of%20xylene%2C%20which%20can%20cause%20headaches%20and%20irritate%20the%20eyes%2C%20nose%20and%20throat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20smoke%20was%20so%20thick%20that%20it%20showed%20up%20on%20Doppler%20radar.%20Firefighters%20were%20told%20to%20leave%20the%20immediate%20area%2C%20and%20residents%20were%20ordered%20to%20shelter%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221297%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20large%20fire%20burns%20at%20K-Solv's%20facility%20in%20Jacintoport%20on%20April%207%2C%202021.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578d81d7a3c8094d5dc4c6d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22805%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20large%20fire%20burns%20at%20K-Solv's%20facility%20in%20Jacintoport%20on%20April%207%2C%202021.%20Despite%20releasing%20thousands%20of%20pounds%20of%20pollutants%20into%20the%20air%2C%20the%20blaze%20barely%20made%20a%20blip%20on%20the%20TCEQ's%20new%20monitor.%3Cp%3EKPRC%202%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECarolyn%20Stone%20and%20her%20husband%20were%20visiting%20family%20when%20people%20started%20calling%20them%20about%20the%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20could%20see%20the%20smoke%20column%20from%20miles%20away%20as%20we%20rushed%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stone%2C%20who%20lives%20less%20than%20a%20mile%20down%20the%20road%20from%20K-Solv.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20wondering%2C%20'Can%20we%20get%20to%20our%20house%3F%20Do%20we%20even%20have%20a%20house%20left%3F%20Were%20our%20pets%20still%20alive%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20house%20was%20undamaged%20and%20their%20pets%20were%20safe.%20But%20a%20layer%20of%20soot%20covered%20their%20yard%2C%20and%20an%20oily%20residue%20coated%20their%20rain%20collection%20barrel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224320%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20oily%20residue%20coats%20a%20rain%20collection%20barrel%20outside%20Carolyn%20Stone's%20home.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578b89a7a3c8094d5dc2f6d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223240%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20oily%20residue%20coats%20a%20rain%20collection%20barrel%20outside%20Carolyn%20Stone's%20home.%20The%20photo%20was%20taken%20on%20April%2013%2C%202021%20%E2%80%94%20six%20days%20after%20a%20chemical%20fire%20at%20K-Solv's%20Jacintoport%20facility.%3Cp%3ECarolyn%20Stone%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fire%20barely%20made%20a%20blip%20on%20the%20TCEQ's%20new%20air%20monitor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%2024%20hours%20after%20the%20fire%2C%20the%20monitor%20showed%20only%20low%20levels%20of%20xylene%20and%20toluene.%20Its%20highest%20one-hour%20benzene%20reading%20was%20just%204.62%20ppb.%20That's%20a%20tiny%20fraction%20of%20the%20many%20one-hour%20benzene%20readings%20Tim%20Doty's%20team%20documented%20outside%20of%20K-Solv%20during%20its%20monitoring%20trips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20day%20after%20the%20fire%2C%20the%20U.S.%20Occupational%20Safety%20and%20Health%20Administration%20began%20an%20inspection%20of%20K-Solv.%20It%20found%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.osha.gov%2Fords%2Fimis%2Festablishment.inspection_detail%3Fid%3D1524334.015%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efive%20violations%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20three%20classified%20as%20%26quot%3Bserious%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20fined%20the%20company%20%2428%2C671.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20TCEQ%20fined%20K-Solv%20%2411%2C413%20for%20the%20fire.%20A%20few%20months%20later%20the%20agency%20opened%20what%20would%20become%20an%20eight-month%20investigation%20into%20the%20company's%20processes%20and%20practices.%20The%20probe%20involved%20at%20least%2015%20agency%20staffers%20and%20included%20on-site%20testing%20and%20inspections%20on%20at%20least%2010%20occasions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20458-page%20investigation%20report%20said%20volatile%20organic%20compounds%20were%20leaking%20from%20two%20large%20tanks.%20At%20least%2020%20more%20leaks%20were%20found%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20compound.%20The%20report%20also%20said%20that%20K-Solv%20had%20stored%20its%20benzene%20reserves%20at%20a%20concentration%20that%20was%20double%20its%20permitted%20limit%20and%20that%20the%20facility's%20vapor%20combustor%2C%20which%20was%20designed%20to%20burn%20toxic%20emissions%20to%20limit%20air%20pollution%2C%20hadn't%20been%20hot%20enough%20to%20work%20properly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20inspectors%20cited%20K-Solv%20for%2014%20violations%2C%20five%20of%20them%20classified%20as%20%26quot%3Bsignificant.%26quot%3B%20K-Solv%20rebutted%20the%20TCEQ's%20findings%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24213934-k-solvs-response-to-tceq%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20273-page%20document%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20company%20shared%20with%20Public%20Health%20Watch.%20It%20denied%20four%20of%20the%20violations%20and%20described%20plans%20to%20fix%20four%20of%20the%20others.%20It%20did%20not%20acknowledge%20the%20remaining%20six.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Carolyn%20Stone%20in%20the%20backyard%20of%20her%20Channelview%2C%20Texas%2C%20home.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578b85b50edbc52a8636d41%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECarolyn%20Stone%20in%20the%20backyard%20of%20her%20Channelview%2C%20Texas%2C%20home.%20She%20leads%20a%20growing%20group%20of%20neighbors%20fighting%20for%20a%20safer%20community%20through%20the%20Channelview%20Health%20%26amp%3B%20Improvement%20Coalition.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20TCEQ%20is%20still%20deciding%20whether%20to%20fine%20the%20company%20for%20the%20violations.%20The%20agency%20didn't%20respond%20when%20Public%20Health%20Watch%20asked%20when%20the%20case%20would%20be%20resolved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20monitor%20installed%20in%202021%20continues%20to%20operate%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20the%20Jacintoport%20neighborhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20the%20first%20full%20year%20it%20was%20operating%2C%20it%20measured%20an%20annual%20benzene%20average%20of%20just%200.79%20ppb%2C%20according%20to%20the%20TCEQ.%20That's%20about%20two-thirds%20less%20than%20the%202.1%20ppb%20the%20old%20metal%20canister%20measured%20from%20the%20middle%20of%20Jacintoport%20in%202020%2C%20its%20last%20full%20year%20of%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EChannelview%20residents%20are%20trying%20to%20organize%20themselves%20to%20defend%20their%20community%20against%20further%20industry%20intrusion.%20It's%20an%20arduous%20process.%20The%20unincorporated%20area%20has%20no%20central%20government%20to%20rally%20behind%2C%20and%20with%20more%20than%2060%25%20of%20residents%20speaking%20a%20language%20other%20than%20English%20at%20home%2C%20there%20are%20wide%20language%20barriers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20Carolyn%20Stone%20formed%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fgroups%2F892294181644780%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChannelview%20Health%20%26amp%3B%20Improvement%20Coalition%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20meets%20at%20the%20local%20fire%20station%20every%20month%20to%20help%20residents%20understand%20the%20environmental%20dangers%20they're%20living%20with%20and%20lobbies%20local%20lawmakers%20to%20step%20up%20to%20protect%20them.%20The%20group%20has%20been%20particularly%20concerned%20about%20the%20San%20Jacinto%20River's%20rapid%20deterioration%20from%20petrochemical%20barge%20activity%2C%20including%20some%20serviced%20by%20K-Solv.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStone%20said%20her%20community%20has%20long%20felt%20abandoned%20by%20the%20TCEQ.%20But%20she%20was%20shocked%20when%20Public%20Health%20Watch%20told%20her%20that%20the%20agency%20had%20known%20for%20years%20about%20high%20benzene%20levels%20in%20Jacintoport%20%E2%80%94%20and%20had%20not%20shared%20that%20information%20with%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20good%20people.%20We're%20not%20trash%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20people%20here%20are%20worthy%20of%20some%20kind%20of%20intervention.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECynthia%20Benson%20is%20part%20of%20Stone's%20group.%20A%20three-time%20cancer%20survivor%2C%20she%20has%20lived%20for%20decades%20in%20her%20family's%20trailer%20park%20a%20quarter%20of%20a%20mile%20from%20K-Solv.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20a%20great%2C%20great%20nephew%20that%20was%20just%20born.%20I%20worry%20about%20him%20growing%20up%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Benson%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20scares%20me%20and%20it%20angers%20me.%20It's%20all%20about%20the%20companies%20and%20the%20almighty%20dollar.%20They%20could%20give%20a%20rat's%20ass%20about%20the%20people%20living%20here.%20How%20do%20I%20make%20peace%20with%20that%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cynthia%20Benson%20fights%20back%20tears%20while%20looking%20out%20at%20petrochemical%20barges%20on%20the%20San%20Jacinto%20River.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578d8f650edbc52a8638a80%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECynthia%20Benson%20fights%20back%20tears%20while%20looking%20out%20at%20petrochemical%20barges%20on%20the%20San%20Jacinto%20River.%20A%20three-time%20cancer%20survivor%20who%20lost%20both%20of%20her%20parents%20to%20the%20disease%2C%20Benson%20wonders%20if%20her%20family%20has%20a%20future%20in%20Channelview.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETim%20Doty%20retired%20from%20the%20TCEQ%20more%20than%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20but%20he%20still%20thinks%20about%20Channelview.%20In%20March%202023%2C%20he%20testified%20before%20the%20Texas%20Legislature%20against%20a%20bill%20that%20ultimately%20failed.%20It%20would%20have%20fined%20residents%20for%20filing%20more%20than%20three%20complaints%20with%20the%20TCEQ%20in%20a%20year%20if%20the%20complaints%20didn't%20result%20in%20enforcement%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20speaking%2C%20Doty%20handed%20legislators%20a%20memo%20that%20included%20the%20following%20paragraph%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPerhaps%20this%20legislation%20is%20intended%20to%20%E2%80%A6%20minimize%20complaints%20from%20the%20Jacintoport%20neighborhood%20in%20Houston%20that%20is%20home%20to%20elevated%20benzene%2C%20a%20known%20carcinogen%2C%20concentrations%20that%20the%20TCEQ%20has%20been%20ignoring%20for%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EK-Solv%20continues%20to%20expand.%20Its%20parent%20company%2C%20K-Solv%20Group%2C%20now%20includes%20at%20least%2020%20subsidiaries%2C%20ranging%20from%20oil-and-gas%20equipment%20businesses%20to%20environmental%20cleanup%20firms.%20The%20original%20facility%20now%20has%2067%20chemical%20storage%20tanks%2C%20nearly%C2%A0quadruple%20what%20it%20had%20in%202005.%20Its%20TCEQ%20air%20permit%20allows%20it%20to%20release%20more%20than%2039%2C000%20pounds%20of%20volatile%20organic%20compounds%2C%20which%20include%20benzene%2C%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20K-Solv%20Group%20opened%20a%20new%20facility%20next%20to%20a%20row%20of%20double-wide%20manufactured%20homes%20and%20about%20900%20feet%20from%20River%20Terrace%20Park%2C%20where%20Channelview%20families%20picnic%20and%20children%20enjoy%20a%20playground%20lined%20with%20swings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20K-Solv%20Wash%20Services%20facility%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578bc770ec98e92f74eac3c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EK-Solv%20Wash%20Services%2C%20which%20opened%20in%20April%2C%20can%20legally%20release%203%2C500%20pounds%20of%20volatile%20organic%20compounds%20into%20the%20air%20each%20year.%20The%20facility%20is%20located%20next%20to%20a%20row%20of%20manufactured%20homes%20and%20just%20down%20the%20road%20from%20River%20Terrace%20Park%2C%20where%20Channelview%20families%20picnic%20and%20children%20enjoy%20a%20popular%20playground.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EK-Solv%20Wash%20Services%20cleans%20tanker%20trucks%20that%20haul%20chemicals%20and%20other%20materials.%20It's%20a%20dirty%20process%20that%20produces%20airborne%20emissions%20and%20toxic%20wastewater.%20According%20to%20its%20TCEQ%20permit%2C%20K-Solv%20Wash%20Services%20can%20legally%20release%203%2C500%20pounds%20of%20volatile%20organic%20compounds%20into%20the%20air%20each%20year.%20That's%20more%20than%20the%20original%20K-Solv%20facility%20was%20allowed%20to%20release%20when%20it%20opened%20back%20in%202004.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETodd%20Riddle%2C%20K-Solv's%20lawyer%2C%20told%20Public%20Health%20Watch%20that%20K-Solv%20Wash%20Services%20has%20%26quot%3Ba%20state%20of%20the%20art%20vapor%20recovery%20system%26quot%3B%20with%20scrubbers%20that%20%26quot%3Bcompletely%20contain%20any%20airborne%20emissions%20of%20any%20kind.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20harmful%20substances%20are%20properly%20contained%20on%20site%20temporarily%20then%20are%20disposed%20of%20offsite%2C%20in%20compliance%20with%20all%20environmental%20regulations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERiddle%20said%20the%20company%20chose%20the%20site%20near%20the%20park%20because%20%26quot%3Bit%20was%20available%20and%20convenient%20and%20served%20our%20purpose.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPublic%20Health%20Watch%20asked%20the%20TCEQ%20if%20it%20considered%20the%20proximity%20of%20the%20park%20and%20the%20houses%20when%20it%20approved%20the%20K-Solv%20Wash%20Services%20permit.%20The%20agency%20declined%20to%20answer%20any%20further%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EReporting%2C%20data%20acquisition%20and%20additional%20work%20contributed%20by%20Jordan%20Gass-Poor%C3%A9%2C%20a%20Public%20Health%20Watch%20audio%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcancer-risk-benzene-pollution-houston-channelview-jacintoport-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702468801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578b48d0ec98e92f74ea5b4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcancer-risk-benzene-pollution-houston-channelview-jacintoport-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Texas%20regulators%20documented%20startling%20amounts%20of%20benzene%20in%20Channelview%2C%20near%20Houston.%20Instead%20of%20solving%20the%20problem%2C%20they%20allowed%20a%20benzene%20polluter%20to%20expand.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(David%20Leffler%2CSavanna%20Strott%2CSalina%20Arredondo%2CJana%20Cholakovska)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A47%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcancer-risk-benzene-pollution-houston-channelview-jacintoport-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Thai%20MP%20jailed%20for%20six%20years%20on%20royal%20insult%20charges%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702468789000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105964700%2Cimgsize-861342.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-