ng%20emotions%20authentically%20without%20compromising%20personal%20comfort.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fkajol-would-never-do-a-molestation-scene-heres-why%2Farticleshow%2F105960573.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mahindra%20and%20Mahindra%2C%20others%20to%20invest%20%24105%20million%20in%20two-wheeler%20unit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702461756000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2020-10%2F12%2Ffull%2F1602524230-5414.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fmahindra-and-mahindra-others-to-invest-105-million-in-two-wheeler-unit-123121300606_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20'Scorpio'%20car%20manufacturer%2C%20will%20invest%205.25%20billion%20and%20the%20remaining%20will%20come%20from%20existing%20shareholders%20and%20new%20investors%2C%20Mahindra%20said%20in%20an%20exchange%20filing%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fmahindra-and-mahindra-others-to-invest-105-million-in-two-wheeler-unit-123121300606_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Governors'%20Pocket%20Veto%20Compromises%20Constitutional%20Probity%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F27102504%2FKolkata%25E2%2580%2599s-Raj-Bhavan-could-be-worth-almost-Rs-2000-crores-today-FB-1200x700-compressed.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2Fp%2Fbjp-disinfo-machine-milking-gaza%5C%22%3Epiece%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20first%20published%20on%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20India%20Cable%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%93%C2%A0a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%C2%A0The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3Eclick%20here%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ERecent%20observation%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20the%20increasing%20tendency%20of%20some%20governors%20to%20hold%20indefinitely%20the%20Bills%20passed%20by%20state%20Assemblies%20has%20far-reaching%20consequences%20in%20strengthening%20the%20federal%20polity%20of%20India.%20If%20this%20had%20happened%20in%20one%20state%2C%20it%20could%20be%20read%20as%20the%20eccentricity%20of%20a%20particular%20individual%20in%20a%20position%20of%20authority.%20When%20a%20similar%20lack%20of%20probity%20is%20seen%20amongst%20the%20constitutional%20heads%20of%20many%20states%20run%20by%20Opposition%20parties%2C%20that%20indicates%20design%20and%20raises%20the%20alarm.%20The%20apex%20court%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpower%20to%20take%20decisions%20affecting%20the%20governance%20of%20the%20state%20or%20the%20nation%20is%20essentially%20entrusted%20to%20the%20elected%20arm%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%9D.%20The%20increasing%20tendency%20of%20governors%20to%20act%20on%20their%20own%2C%20ignoring%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%2C%20is%20like%20%E2%80%9Cplaying%20with%20fire%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20present%20impasse%20in%20many%20Opposition-run%20states%20reminds%20us%20of%20a%20similar%20incident%20at%20the%20national%20level%20almost%20four%20decades%20ago%2C%20when%20the%20relationship%20between%20prime%20minister%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20and%20president%20Giani%20Zail%20Singh%20had%20reached%20a%20nadir%20and%20that%20almost%20created%20a%20constitutional%20deadlock.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EArticle%2074(1)%20of%20the%20constitution%20states%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccouncil%20of%20ministers%20headed%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%20shall%20aid%20and%20advise%20the%20president%20in%20the%20exercise%20of%20his%20duties%E2%80%9D.%20Is%20that%20advice%20binding%20on%20the%20president%3F%20The%2042nd%20Amendment%20(1976)%20of%20the%20constitution%20made%20the%20advice%20binding.%20However%2C%20the%2044th%20Amendment%20(1978)%20stated%20that%20the%20president%20can%20send%20the%20advice%20back%20to%20the%20council%20for%20reconsideration%20for%20once.%20If%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%20sends%20the%20same%20advice%20again%20to%20the%20president%2C%20he%20must%20accept%20it.%20Is%20there%20any%20time%20limit%20prescribed%20in%20the%20constitution%20for%20the%20president%20to%20accept%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%3F%20Unfortunately%2C%20that%20is%20not%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EPresident%20Giani%20Zail%20Singh%20did%20not%20give%20his%20assent%20to%20the%20Indian%20Post%20Office%20(Amendment)%20Bill%20(1986)%20after%20the%20Bill%20was%20passed%20in%20Parliament.%20He%20sat%20on%20the%20Bill%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20tenure%2C%20which%20created%20a%20kind%20of%20constitutional%20impasse%20at%20that%20time.%20Was%20it%20ethical%20of%20the%20president%20to%20veto%20a%20Bill%20passed%20by%20Parliament%3F%20Such%20an%20impasse%20did%20not%20recur%2C%20not%20even%20when%20the%20incumbent%20presidents%20were%20from%20a%20political%20party%20opposed%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%20at%20the%20Centre%20%E2%80%95%20K.R.%20Narayanan%20during%20NDA-1%20or%20Pranab%20Mukherjee%20during%20NDA-2%20rule.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20supremacy%20of%20parliament%20in%20Indian%20democracy%20was%20established.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fgovernors-as-ruling-partys-storm-troopers%5C%22%3EGovernors%20as%20Ruling%20Party%E2%80%99s%20Storm%20Troopers%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20present%20trend%20of%20a%20few%20governors%20keeping%20Bills%20passed%20by%20Assemblies%20pending%20indefinitely%20undermines%20the%20authority%20of%20elected%20governments.%20Under%20Article%20201%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20a%20Bill%20can%20be%20reserved%20by%20the%20governor%20for%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20president%2C%20if%20the%20content%20of%20the%20Bill%20has%20national%20ramifications.%20The%20president%20may%20give%20his%20assent%2C%20may%20withhold%20or%20even%20send%20back%20a%20Bill%20to%20the%20governor%2C%20with%20the%20direction%20to%20return%20it%20to%20the%20state%20Assembly%20for%20reconsideration.%20However%2C%20if%20the%20governor%20has%20not%20reserved%20the%20Bill%20for%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20president%2C%20he%20has%20to%20act%20as%20per%20Article%20200%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EArticle%20200%20of%20the%20Constitution%20clearly%20states%20that%20once%20a%20Bill%20is%20passed%20in%20the%20state%20Assembly%20and%20presented%20to%20the%20governor%2C%20he%20or%20she%20must%20either%20approve%20the%20Bill%20or%20return%20it%20with%20a%20request%20to%20the%20House%20to%20%E2%80%9Creconsider%20the%20Bill%20or%20any%20specified%20provisions%20thereof%E2%80%9D.%20According%20to%20the%20apex%20court%2C%20the%20governor%20has%20to%20do%20so%20%E2%80%9Cas%20soon%20as%20possible%E2%80%9D.%20If%20the%20House%20passes%20the%20Bill%20after%20reconsideration%20with%20or%20without%20amendment%2C%20and%20the%20Bill%20is%20presented%20to%20the%20governor%20for%20the%20second%20time%2C%20he%20shall%20not%20withhold%20assent.%20Article%20200%20did%20not%20fix%20any%20timeline%20for%20the%20governor%20to%20decide%20on%20the%20matter.%20That%20loophole%20is%20being%20used%20by%20Raj%20Bhavans%20for%20deliberate%20procrastination.%20The%20apex%20court%20observed%20that%20governors%20cannot%20sit%20on%20Bills%20indefinitely%20without%20disclosing%20reasons%20for%20delay.%20Though%20the%20constitution%20provides%20complete%20immunity%20to%20governors%20from%20court%20proceedings%2C%20they%20cannot%20act%20arbitrarily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Sarkaria%20Commission%2C%20set%20up%20in%201983%20to%20examine%20Centre-state%20relations%2C%20had%20recommended%20that%20%E2%80%9Ca%20governor%20should%20be%20eminent%20in%20some%20walks%20of%20life%20and%20not%20too%20intimately%20connected%20with%20local%20politics%20of%20the%20state%2C%20and%20he%20should%20be%20a%20person%20who%20has%20not%20taken%20too%20great%20a%20part%20in%20politics%2C%20in%20general%2C%20and%20in%20the%20recent%20past%20in%20particular%E2%80%9D.%20Unfortunately%2C%20these%20guidelines%20were%20never%20taken%20seriously%20by%20subsequent%20Union%20governments.%20The%20Union%20government%20will%20hopefully%20be%20more%20judicious%20in%20the%20future%20about%20selecting%20governors%2C%20after%20what%20has%20been%20said%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Governors%20of%20the%20states%20also%20need%20to%20learn%20from%20the%20precedents%20created%20by%20presidents%20of%20the%20republic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EGautam%20Bhattacharya%20is%20a%20former%20university%20teacher%20and%20former%20additional%20secretary%20to%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702461630000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F27102504%2FKolkata%25E2%2580%2599s-Raj-Bhavan-could-be-worth-almost-Rs-2000-crores-today-FB-1200x700-compressed.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgovernors-pocket-veto-compromises-constitutional-probity%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20tendency%20of%20governors%20sitting%20indefinitely%20on%20Bills%20cleared%20by%20state%20Assemblies%20raises%20alarm.%20When%20a%20lack%20of%20probity%20is%20seen%20amongst%20the%20constitutional%20heads%20of%20many%20states%20run%20by%20Opposition%20parties%2C%20it%20indica